reviews.text: Never had a problem with any Target except this one. Time before last when elderly couple had problem using their atm, I had to wait with my daughter over 1/2 an hour, while over 25 customers at other registers went ahead. I counted. No other register said oh I'll take you since there was a problem with the customer ahead of us. The lady at the register did not bother taking us ahead or asking another rep. at another register to help us like other Targets would do. Meanwhile, even though I may look young and my daughter is young, my daughter's major health problem was affecting her while we waited, but since we look young they just left us waiting for over a half hour. Additionally, the last time I went there was the 5th time their sale prices kept ringing up as full price. So, I took a picture of the sales prices and showed the cashier. She didn't believe me. Yet, at other Targets they would just correct the matter right away without a picture of course. She made my daughter and I wait over 1/2 hour and took other customers ahead of us. I waited again while my daughter was almost passing out due to her health problem. Then, the rep. was rude and acted like it was our fault they did not honor their listed sale prices plain as day in their store. She made us wait there and look like idiots when she took several customers ahead of us. She even acted like she was doing me a favor when she verified that they put the wrong sale price tag on the wrong product, but would give me the sale price this time. I'm sorry, but how am I supposed to know they put their sale price on the wrong product of theirs? That was 100 percent their error. They list sale prices and then scam customers and ring up their products full price, and then make you look like you are wrong? Again, this was the 5th visit that this happened to us. So, I will never shop at this Target again.

reviews.text: My husband went in to pick up a gift for a bridals shower. When he printed the girl's registry he specifically set it to filter the list to what is available at this location. The records this store keeps on its inventory however are so terrible that the registry list sent him on a wild goose chase. He asked 3 separate workers for help. 1 had no idea and 2 flat out refused to help saying it wasn't their dept with shrugs....WHAT? Having worked at Targets before I can guarantee you that this was handled outside of company policy. As a result my husband ran out of time and had to leave empty handed. I'll have to make another trip now to the Super Target farther away to get a gift in time.

I had an awful experience at your store. I recent bought some furniture with you, (an 8 cube shelf) I was really excited about it! When I got it home I discovered that the box was a return that had been put back on the shelf. I hoped that whoever returned it just decided that they didn't want it, so I checked all the parts to make sure everything was there, and it was so I started putting it together. I went to pick up the bottom piece in the box and discovered that the back of it had huge chunks missing out of it. I was pretty irritated that it was put back on the shelf, damaged and returned, how ridiculous that NO ONE had checked before putting it back on the floor. I called the store to get another one brought up and I asked them to open and check to make sure it wasn't damaged. When I got there I asked the customer service representative again if it had been opened and checked, she LIED to my face saying that they had. Then she began to complain to me about how she was supposed to be on her lunch, being incredibly unfriendly to me the entire transaction, making me feel unwanted and uncomfortable. After she finished the transaction, she set my receipt on the counter, took the box and walked away, without saying a word to me.
When I got home to start putting the shelf together, I found that the box was beat up but still sealed and this one was also damaged, there's a huge gash on the side. At this point I have no idea what to do, but I'm fed up with the way I've been treated. i understand that customer service isn't the easiest job, I worked in retail for 4 years, but there is no excuse to act like that. I may have been a little irritated, but I never took it out on her and I don't believe I was unreasonable in the situation.
11-10-2012
Awesome they had everything I needed

What a disappointment. My Fiancee and I went here to register for our wedding and were treated so poorly. We were handed a scanning gun & then the associate just walked away. She didn't explain how it worked, where we could find anything, or whom to speak with if we had any questions. The gentleman who worked in electronics was hardly a gentleman at all; he kept referring to nicer cameras as "sick" but couldn't explain why they were better than the rest. The scanning gun only worked on a few items, and nobody ever asked if we needed any help with anything. To say the least, I was sorely disappointed. We went to Bed Bath & Beyond afterwards and were treated like gold. I wouldn't recommend this specific Target to anybody I know.

reviews.text: Love  this place.  Prob the best hotel and room I've ever stayed at.  I stay at a ton of Hyatt for business but this one was amazing.   The room was very modern and the shower and tub was amazing.  Def someplace I would like to stay again.

I got the opportunity to stay at the Andaz Wall Street during a business trip. This is not a hotel I'd typically stay at myself as it does run on the pricier end. However, I was more than happy to take advantage during my business trip. The hotel is very very nice, sleek and modern. The decor is beautiful. The service was great and super helpful when I asked for coffee refills and they pointed out the free water in the lobby. My room was great. The bed super comfy, the shower was giant with an overhead shower head as well as having a removable handheld shower spray (not sure what it's called). The best part was the mini fridge with free non-alcoholic drinks that were refilled everyday along with some free granola/protein bars and chips. The giant window was also awesome as I was able to move the sun shade up and down by a touch of a button by my bedside and there were buttons to dim some or all the lights. This hotel is awesome.

Great hotel at an amazing price. Stayed for 2 nights in May 2014. Beautiful, modern rooms. Got upgraded for free just by asking if there was one available. All the drinks and snacks in the room are free except for alcohol. The shower and bath is not private (you can see in through the glass in the room) so maybe not good for family/friends but perfect for couples or single stay. Location was great, walking distance to Staten Island Ferry, Battery Park/Statue of Liberty Ferry, subway stations and The World Trade Center memorial. Lots of great places to eat and drink close by and there are always cabs out front. We'll be staying here next time we visit for sure!

by far, the best room I have been in NYC, price was fine taking in account the rest of the hotels in NYC, convenient for work meetings as it is in Wall Street, bars, restaurants, everything is walking distance. A bit too far from most of NYC attractions, but the subway will take you there if you want to do tourism.
the room, bed, shower, tub, furniture, everything was to an excellent standard, modern looking, impeccable. Andaz is always a sure bet

Great business hotel!

Came here on Christmas Holidays in 2012 with my girlfriend. We're from Italy. When we came in a very kind guy offer us a room upgrade... FOR FREE. I was like... mmm... to good to be true... but it was actually true!!! Very big room, snack and non alcoholic drink for free. Huge shower. Out of the chaotic side of Manhattan, and near to Battery Park if I have to come back to The City I'll definitely choose Andaz Wall Street once again. Great and kind staff, excellent location (IMHO) and very good value.

reviews.text: All I could say in spite of the fact that the hotel registration was very busy on the weekend we held our conference, they managed to accommodate our needs. Especially the front desk manager Felicia who made me feel that I was being well taken care of. She went above & beyond just to provide for all my needs during this conference. Felicia is awesome!
Rooms could use refrigerators and microwaves. Other than that, the rooms are comfortable and the staff is helpful.
Pathetic service, front desk guy was very rude, bathroom flush broken, $22 for parking per night, no amenities as simple as microwave, and you have to pay for wifi. Not coming back again

Besides the proximity to the Airport, the one thing that made this hotel THE BEST, was the service.  These people went above and beyond to make our stay AH-MAZING.  First of all, when we got here, we were greeted by a man at the door.  Then, when we checked in, the people at the front desk actually smiled and were nice to us.  That never happens at a hotel.  I realized at one point that I forgot my phone charger.  I went to the front desk to ask if they knew of a store or anywhere around where I could purchase one.  The young lady actually called her maids to see if they possibly had one I could borrow...and they did.  THEN, I came down the next morning to see if there was complimentary coffee in the cafe.  There wasn't, but the front desk young lady (a different one) said, "you know what, I'm going to gift you a cup of coffee.  it's on me."  THEN, we had to extend our stay...not an entire night, just by a few hours... most hotels make you purchase an entire hotel stay...the woman at the desk (different from the first two) said, "I will just extend it.  if you have to stay another night, then we'll charge you, but if it's just a few hours, i'm not going to make you pay."   This place was all around amazing...I kinda wanna live here.

One of the WORST Hotel experiences in 15 years.  had to stay here as a result of a canceled connecting flight.  Made reservation via smartphone at terminal, got confirmation e-mail, showed up at front desk, woman could not locate my reservation despite confirmation e-mail i showed her.  She did not EVEN offer a room, I had to ASK if they had available rooms since she could not find my reservation, she informed me that I will probably get double charged "or something".  I was so exhausted from traveling I didn't even bother arguing the issue, ended up with a dirty horrible smelling room near the main elevator bank and hallway ice machine (had to listen to loud noise from both all night).............I can't believe this has the HILTON name on it......should be changed to Motel 6 with pricing cut by 2/3.

reviews.text: I have to admit, their beef fajita's are wonderful! I spent several months back in the 90's down on the Texas Border where the Mexican Food is so Authentic, anywhere you buy it (i.e. 7/11, convenience stores, etc) that Taco Bells or Johns (pretend Mexican Food) would never make it there, so I never saw those businesses. This Store is a diamond in the rough. My son went to get me one of their Steak Burritos one day, & I've been going there ever since. To bad they don't have delivery though ;(
Totally the best Mexican food in Janesville! Small place only 6 tables but great food & great service! They do take out and you can call ahead.

Delicious food for even the most picky eater. The staff is more than willing to help describe the menu to unfamiliar customers. I've eaten here on a regular basis for the last 4 years. Most authentic Mexican food in Janesville!
great food and service

If you want the authentic flavor of Mexico, come to La Fiesta Mexicana on Main Street.  A recent article by Tracy Douglas in the Gazette touted the virtues of their food, but she obviously did not stop by on Saturday or Sunday - the traditional days when small bodegas like La Fiesta serve carnitas - roast pig and menudo (a spicy soup) that will make you cry it is so delicious.  This family owned and operated grocery store is staffed by warm, friendly people (who patiently put up with my fractured Spanish) and is chock full of good Mexican groceries and beautiful meats including fresh shrimp and fish.  I have been shopping and dining there for several years now and find the restaurant prices to be startlingly low, the quality of the produce good, the meats excellent, and the service outstanding.  This is a marvelous slice of Mexico right here in Janesville.  LOVE it.

reviews.text: Always shop here. Yes you can probably buy a lot of the stuff a little cheaper elsewhere; but the customer service level, and cleanliness of the place makes up for it.  It is nice to go into a store to buy something and not have to be bothered with some of the rift raft that populates other stores. Plus, when they do have a promotion no other store can beat it.

Harris Teeter sells basically the same stuff as any other market but they like to charge 25%+ more than their competitors. I'm not sure why people shop there. It's where you shop if money doesn't matter to you.

Up until recently, I have always used Harris Teeter at Hollymead Center as my go to grocery store (now, for reasons detailed in this review, I will only be shopping there when there is a sale + coupon that would make an item wholesale price or less-- they will no longer profit off of my business). I take advantage of their "super doubles" promotion where they double coupons up to $2.00 for a week often because my family is of very modest means, just barely over the income line for state assistance for "needy" families, and we have to make cutbacks wherever we can (though I do also purchase items there full price). I also shop for my in-laws, who are shut-ins, using their money and their Harris Teeter card. Recently, after a two hour long shopping trip, the manager came over after I had already finished checking out, cancelled the entire transaction and made me put everything back, informing me that she knew I was exceeding the limit of 20 doubled coupons per household by using two different cards. Um, yes, I informed her, but half of these groceries are for a different household, purchased with that household's money and that household's card. Further, the members of that household cannot leave their home to go shopping, and depend people like me and my wife to shop for them. The way the manager was speaking to me, I don't think even a sworn affidavit along with a visit to my in-laws' house herself would have changed her mind. So, if you're one of the millions of people in the US that has elderly friends or relatives that cannot leave their home (and therefore cannot shop for themselves), be warned that Harris Teeter will only allow you to shop there using coupons for either your own household OR the household that you are helping, not both! As an added bonus, they'll also treat you like a perpetrator of fraud. Congratulations, Harris Teeter, you've just denied an elderly couple who can't leave their house an affordable source of food, and you've lost yourself a loyal customer.
J

reviews.text:
EJ's is a quaint, classic diner set-up residing on the Upper East Side. I used to frequent here during my lunch time since it was so close to my job. Yes, it's typical diner fare. However, they have items with fun, unique twists. Breakfast, brunch, lunch... it's all there. Regarding breakfast foods, my go-to was the cereal corn flake crusted french toast with blueberry compote. It was crispy, crunchy and that warm compote just elevated the flavors perfectly! I am also a huge fan of their breakfast skillets. For lunch, I recommend their burgers. They're a classic option and overall delicious!

P.S. Fun fact: They're featured in Something Borrowed: Emily Giffin!
almost empty restaurant they forced us to eat in a corner against our request. very rude and unaccommodating to anything we asked for. we left without ordering. plenty of real restaurant in the area.

Very good milk shakes but when I went to their bathroom I was so disgusted. Sticky floors, no toilet paper, no soap and everything is wet with god knows what. And on top of that all the toilets were clogged! I got to this diner all the time and the bathrooms always disappoint me.

Once again, they screwed up my delivery order.  The correct one never came and apparently EJ's no longer can be bothered to scrape off the grill between orders.  Not the restaurant it used to be,  I can only assume that at some point management was taken over by pirates since piracy is not a very customer service-orientated field.  EJ's has seen the last of me, I order food because I don't want something that tastes like sugary onions and a burnt rubber glove.

After a long day, I was walking down 3rd Avenue looking for a place to grab a quick bite, and the interior of  EJ's caught my eye and I grabbed a stool and ate a nice and juicy bacon cheeseburger that hit the spot. Atmosphere was nice, staff was attentive and friendly, and the food came out quickly. Throw in a little 80's music playing in the background, and I was a very happy camper!

reviews.text: Unique among kosher restaurants for having different foods and cheeses besides the great service (another unique quality)

tremendously horrible service. dare I say it,  but new yorkers don't know the first thing about customer service, so to have bad customer service in new york is well, atrocious to say the least. and the food wasnt too good either.

So I was on a date there and we order our food.  the place is next to empty but we don't get any food.  Finally after 20 or 30 minutes I ask the waitress where the food was.  She was surprised we didn't have it.  All she had to do was turn her head for 3 seconds and stop shmuzzing and she would see that.  Apparently there was a mistake and the order was never put through.  Apparently she was very good at taking the order, just not giving the order to the cook. 

When I finally received my order, my tzatziki looked and tasted like sour cream.  I asked the manager she took it back asked the chef and he confirmed that it was tzatziki.  I kept using and again i remarked that it was sour cream.  this time they took it back and gave me real tzatiki.  I was given some weird explanation that didn't really make any sense.

anyways after getting such poor service, i asked for a complimentary dessert and I was refused.

I had made up my mind and had no intention of leaving a good tip.  However when my check came the tip was pre calculated in it.

On top of all this, the food is really expensive.

Would not go back here

WAY overpriced, Service sucked and the food is just O K. My wife and I already decided "Never Again"

reviews.text: This is my favorite grocery store in all of Charlotte. This store has the widest variety of produce, meat, dairy, and international items out of any store in the entire state. reviews.text: I love these guys. Order online for even better deals. When I get to checkout, I almost always find "surprise" discounts, like "$10 Tuesdays" and "$12 Family Size" discounts. reviews.text:
Dominick's staff are very, very nice. 

The meat is very affordable, but other items do cost more. Delivery...not so good. Been waiting 4.5 hours (and still waiting going on 5 hours), stuck at home, unable to go anywhere. 

. Had to cancel something I very much needed to do, because I'm waiting on these people. And calls are totally unhelpful! You might as well ask them to fly to the moon. 

Also, the store wasn't as clean as it could be, and some of the displays were positively slovenly.. No excuse for that, in my book. Particularly scary looking were the open freezer chests in two locations inside the store. 

I'm sure the locals love it, and I do like the staff there, and not to sound like a food snob, but really-- the cramped and sloppy conditions were sort of off-putting for my taste. They seemed to have enough staff that someone could make the time to go through the freezer chests & shelves and straighten things up, make it look more professional. 

Some of the meat didn't look so hot, either. YOu have to really look it over good--not to say the cuts were bad, they were quite good, but I could see some meat turning brown, which if the sell-by date was correct, shouldn't have happened. Won't pretend to know what's going on with that. 

Will I go back there? Probably. If only for the meat prices. But I likely won't bother with delivery, since they aren't very professional about it. 

But that's actually the norm for Syracuse, where every other business is run half-baked.

I was very happy when I walked into this place and found a nice clean grocery mart, when so many others in the area are drab and dirty. The store was a little cramped as it was busy but the service was great, and the meat was reasonably priced. I was also surprised by how broad of a selection of goods they were able to offer.

I order my Meat Packages from here. Saves me a Bundle vs getting meat at a chain grocer. I had stopped ordering for a long time when I called to place an order recently the Lady remembered who I was it was very nice. It had been almost a year since I used them. 2 thumbs up 5 stars.

reviews.text: I have been a Fred's customer for years, overall the prices are very reasonable.  recently, my local Fred's in Poplar Bluff, MO, has been very disappointing. It is several dollars cheaper than Nyquil and even a dollar cheaper than the Dollar General Store brand.  Fred's is just more convenient to my apartment.  I have been forced to take my business elsewhere simply because they will make no attempt to order more.  The end of last week the cashier told me the truck would be in Wednesday and Today is Wednesday and guess what was not on the truck.  When I went in last week, the big box, at least 18 inches in length, was empty.  I moved the box from the bottom shelf onto the top to check behind it.  The huge box sat on the top shelf 3 entire days before they moved it.  Yes, I checked on the medicine for three days before asking about it because the employees are not extremely friendly nor accessible..  I was given false hopes once I had asked.  The Poplar Bluff store, and employees are a disappointment.  Luckily, there is a Dollar General Store only minutes away.Due to poor organization and proper ordering skills, I am severing my long term relationship with the Poplar Bluff Store.

reviews.text: I have now taken two trips with Gate1 Travel.  In each case, the entire experience was excellent.  Each of the guides was helpful, knowledgeable and really made the trip fun.  Each one went out of his way on every detail to enhance the experience.  The accommodations were well planned and,I think were among the best available everywhere we went.  The best testimonial I can give is that on each trip, we met experienced travelers who had been on anywhere from 5-9 Gate 1 trips.  We can't wait to go again.

My wife and I just got back from 11 day Croatia/Slovenia in March this year. We have joined 11 Gate 1 tours to three continents (Europe, Asia and South Africa) since 2012.  They were all outstanding and the tour guides were excellent and very knowledgeable. We are going to see Greece with Gate 1 again in May 2015. We did travel with other well known tour companies too but found Gate 1 to be superior in its price, itinerary, hotels and especially service. Gate 1 is the only company that makes flexible arrangements for starting and ending the trips.  We are seniors and feel comfortable that there is always a Gate 1 representative to receive us at the airport  upon arrival and get us to the airport any time, even 2 am in the morning or 11pm at night. We trust Gate 1  because we know we are always in good hands in a foreign country. We recommend it most highly to anybody who wants to travel.

We recently took a Gate1 tour of Spain visiting Madrid, Granada, Toledo, Seville, and Barcelona.  The trip was fabulous, as all of our Gate1 trips have been!  The tour guide and the local guides were extremely knowledgeable.  We saw and learned so much.  The hotels we stayed in were excellent and the buffet breakfasts outstanding.  My group of ladies have traveled with Gate1 many times and have never been disappointed.  Their tours are always well-planned and well-executed at a very fair price.  We will soon book another trip with them for the Fall!

My husband and I had a wonderful trip visiting Thailand and Cambodia  (15 days).
That was our first  experience traveling with the group and everything was above our expectation. Starting with very easy booking process online, perfect flight connection (just one stop for 1,5 hour in Tokyo), choice of hotels and trip itinerary . Gate 1 takes you places of the beaten track-we visited local school, had dinner at the Thai family home, got a ride on an ox-cart and visited floating fishing villages. 
A large part of the great experience for the tour can be attributed to very knowledgeable, professional tour guide Steven. 
We got excellent value for our money spent , I am  going to plan my future trips with Gate 1 and recommend it to my friends.

After an uneventful flight on Delta and KLM to Milan, we took the Gate 1 supplied ground transportation to Como, Italy. Later that night we met with our tour guide Daniela
at the hotel. She is an excellent and engaging tour guide but then we expected no less from Gate 1 as our other 3 tour guides were also excellent. For the next 14 days on our tour of Italy, we saw and experienced the beautiful and romantic country and it's people.
Our hotels were perfectly located in the cities we visited and the meals provided during our tour were good. This was the perfect tour to experience the highlights of the country. Everything worked out as intended. We highly recommend this tour to anyone who wants to experience Italy and it's culture.

reviews.text:
I was looking for a commuter vehicle with decent gas mileage.  Darin figured out our needs and desires quickly, pointed out some great options, and never once made us feel pressured about the process.  The rate was right where we wanted and the process went smooth.  

The next day after taking our chosen vehicle home, something went wrong with the center display.  Taking it back in, they were both embarrassed, surprised, and prompt in getting it fixed and me on my way.  It could have been a terrible situation, but they handled the situation perfectly.  It's hard to tell character when everything goes smooth.  I got to see them when things went wrong and they earned that fantastic rating.

I was looking for a new Prius. I Knew from previous buying experience with my salesman Brent Palmatier that I would get a good deal on any vehicle I chose, no pressure.
There is a reason he has been working there for years, he treats his customers right. He genuinely cares about his customers even after the sale to see if they are happy with their purchase and to answer any questions that they may have. I'm completely satisfied with my new Prius. I would definitely buy another Toyota from Brent.

This is the 3rd car I have purchased from Peterson Toyota, and all three times Brent Palmatier has been an excellent sales consultant who helped me find what I was looking for. Brent has been patient and understanding while helping me find what I needed, with no typical "pushy" car salesman type gimmicks. Peterson Toyota has been upfront about all costs and very helpful with all my purchases there. I expect to continue to purchase from them for years to come. 
Thanks Brent and Peterson Toyota!

If I could give this dealership a 0 I would.  The only redeeming quality about Peterson Toyota is their sales team.

I am an Active Duty Air Force Medic.  I don't have much money, but was looking into trading in my unreliable car for something in better shape in preparation for an upcoming transition.  Thinking that Peterson Toyota was a reputable dealership, I figured I would be in good hands.  As it turns out, Peterson Toyota is a money grubbing dealership that has scumbag managers. They don’t give a crap that what they sold me was a chunk of metal death trap that was disguised as a car. They don’t care that the used “car” they sold me was supposed to go to auction and should have NEVER been sold at their dealership. They think that it’s ok to put a piece of poo safety hazard on their lot, slap their name on it to deceive trusting customers into thinking it’s a quality car and then, when it breaks down less than 24 hours later, hide behind the fact that is was sold “as is”. Now the money that I have been saving the past few months to pay my bills during my transition, visit my recently widowed mother and fix a leak under my house is all going to a new transmission instead. Thank you Peterson Toyota.  This money that would have been pocket change to your dealership affects my whole life. If you are in Idaho, or have any family or friends in the local area, please do them a favor and tell them to avoid the Peterson Toyota dealership off of Fairview.

I am a deliberate buyer and researched ALL full size trucks to determine what vehicle would meet my camping and hunting activity.  Finally, when I landed on a Toyota Tundra, I searched all dealerships in the western US.  There were some better advertised sale prices in a couple dealerships up north but I prefer to buy local.  I met with Curt Knipe on a couple occasions, but previous to being ready to pull the trigger.  After deciding the truck type/accessories we wanted, we went to Petersons to have a serious discussion about the Tundra TRD they had on the lot.  Curt was professional and engaged.  I explained my research and what I was willing to pay for the truck.  The initial counter offer was close but not yet where I wanted it to be. Curt kept up the advocacy on our behalf and we reached a win/win deal.  After signing, we met several representatives from the local insurance agent, accessories department representative, and service manager.  We appreciate their engagement and information. Curt reviewed with us the truck accessories and paired my cell phone to the Bluetooth device.  Great teamwork everyone!  We look forward to many fun filled years with our Tundra TRD.

I think these people are running a fraud game here....Imagine how many people this may have happened to that dont do something about it? Well they got the wrong one here!!!

These Owners do not respect the community they do business in and therefore should not be patronized. Go to another mom and pop store that cares about their customers!! Put money in honest peoples pockets, NOT THESE THIEVES!!!

We attempted to get resolve that night and after telling us it was our problem, she hung up on us then took the phone off the hook!

Dont give these people your hard earned money!

reviews.text:
This Walmart location is an Disneyland adventure for every shopper of any age, culture or national origin! Luckily my Spanish was good enough to ask about certain items, alas, the Spanish-speaking workers (which are most of them) still didn't know where anything was. The Haitian Creole speaking workers are always angry and pissed they have to work there (well, who wouldn't be?), so trying to guessing if that black employee will be American or Caribbean is a fun game/thrill ride!

Another thrilling game is "Guess-What-You'll-Pay?" As most items have no price posted on the shelf (if they're on the correct shelf in the first place), you get to decide on the spot if you are willing to pay $5, $10 or over $50! It all comes together at the cashier's when you find out exactly what it costs. Don't try to find one of the price checkers and God forbid you try to ask one of the workers where one is (Spanish= "yo no se!" and Haitian Creole/French=silent blank, angry stares).

Keep an eye on your shopping cart because if you leave it out of sight for a few minutes, it'll disappear. I don't think it's one of the workers taking it to put the items back in the totally wrong places. I'm guessing one of the unwashed masses that shop there just take the cart, dump the contents out on the nearest shelf and do their own shopping (instead of taking a cart when they enter the store) because the average customer there seems to have the IQ of a shopping cart... except the carts have some use to society.

When the time comes to escape and drive out of the parking lot, be very careful as there will be a.) a car parked right behind you as they the driver tries to remember where they are and what they are doing there, b.) 14 people will be climbing out of the car, even if it's not right by the entrance to the store, or c.) a person or persons are walking in the middle of the lane at a pace of 1 mile per week, totally oblivious to the fact they're in the middle of a parking lot.

Of course, the usual three police cars parked in the front of the building is a testament to the safety and kind of customers you will find here. Shop online if at all possible and count the shipping charges as a luxury for not having to go to this location.

Is this the most ghetto walmart in the country or just this city? Their lines stretch to the clothing department because idiots there decide to man only four registers, barely any of their shopping carts are usable and litter the parking lot, and I fear for my life walking in and out of that s***hole. Why waste three hours of my life when inevitably I end up frustrated and simply leave?

We get you pay your workers nothing and have no problem putting them into abject poverty but this is clearly destroying your customer service. I'm on my way out the door to Costco.

My mom was so upset with me when I asked her to do a site to store pick up from this location. She said customer service is awful and they just walk by you. I did call the phone and asked a very nice lady on the phone to help my mother out. She paged someone right away. I'm saying its OK cause I love Walmart and I miss it since I live in Brooklyn now and have no Walmart:(

I shop the West Hartford CT store.   It is smaller than some other TJs I have visited, and therefore has a smaller selection.  What they do have is good and less expensive than other markets, especially Whole Foods.  Staff members have always gone out of their way to be helpful, and they have always been friendly.  I enjoy the somewhat playful atmosphere.

They have some products labeled as gluten free, but I would like to see more of them.  I took off a star for that lack, but then I placed it back for how helpful and prompt staff are when I make a special order.

This store is perfect for those who want cheap organic/all natural foods w/o the Whole Foods prices or the Stop & Shop grandiose nastiness. Of course, there is the problem with TJs occasionaly not having what you need and you having to stop at Whole Foods on the way home for a thing or two. But I  I love TJs becuase its small and I dont feel like I'm part of the machine when I'm shopping there. And I've never experienced anything but friendly and professional staff there.

reviews.text: I stopped at this Shell station around 6 pm after work.  The female cashier was very unfriendly.  Never greeted me as a customer, didn't say thank you,  the store was filthy.  Will never stop there again

I went to the Shell Station on E. Broadway around 10:45am (6-28-2013) and used my credit card for gas.  I pumped $11.04 worth of gas into my car and went on my way.  Around 4:00pm, I checked my bank statement online and noticed an UNAUTHORIZED charge from Shell station 2180 E. Broadway for $50.00.  I immediately called the store to inquire about the charges and was met with nothing but a "I don't care attitude from the Manager, Yajaia.  She told me she would research it but because it had been almost 6 hours, she wouldn't be able to get back to me until the morning (6-29-2013).  I told her that was unacceptable and would be calling her at 7pm if I hadn't heard back.  Here we are at 9:00pm and I haven't heard anything back.  I called again and they refuse to answer the phone.  Either they have turned the ringer off OR they are refusing to answer my phone call.  

I highly recommend you do not use this gas station (there are a few stations about a half mile west of this station) but if it is imperative you get gas here, pay INSIDE and get a recipe.

reviews.text: Called to make an appointment.   They were booked out 2 weeks.   They came highly recommended so took the appointment. We just had Sergio come to our house and fix a break in our yard.  Sergio called before he arrived, asked if it was convenient to fix the break at this time, showed up promptly, and was very professional and polite.  He fixed the break in no time and we are VERY HAPPY!    With 100 degree weather we were very concerned about plants and Sergio saved the day!
Ed Gonzales was fast, friendly, and effective! He fixed a persistent leak at my house in about 30 minutes, and he arrived about 5 minutes from the time I called. Great job, Ed!

This was our best experience with Just Sprinklers. They are always efficient, knowledgeable, and handle any issues on the spot. This time, however, we were really impressed with Sergio V.  He arrived early in the morning, as we had requested and got to work quickly. He checked every zone and nearly every drip, spray and bubbler. He dug out drips and sprinkers on plant to see that they worked. He adjusted sprinker heads to make sure the spray zones were hitting the right areas...getting one off our back window.  He was respectful, diligent and a pleasure to work with. We will ask for Sergio by name the next time. Thanks!!  Linda

Thank you so much, Just Sprinklers, and your technicians, Carlos and Juan, for the great work you did at my house!  Your techs were on time, were dressed in your uniform, were professional and polite.  Before the work started, Carlos, Juan and I reviewed what I wanted done so that we were all on the same page.  They worked very efficiently and were done with a difficult job in record time.  I was so impressed with how "smart" they worked!  When they were finished they cleaned up my place very nicely -- left it in perfect condition!  I couldn't be more pleased!  Keep up the good work and congratulations on a job well done!!!

BURNSVILLE, Minn. — A Burnsville store clerk is accused of threatening a man with a baseball bat after the man asked if he could fill up his water bottle.

Forty-seven-year-old Mahmoud Ahmed Alsharif of Rosemount is charged with terroristic threats.

According to the complant, the man, his girlfriend and her 4-year-old son entered Super Gas USA last Wednesday. Alsharif told the man that the bathroom and faucet were only for customers.

The woman says Asharif also was angry that the boy had used the bathroom. She says the clerk rejected her attempt to buy juice.

Alsharif allegedly raised his hand in the shape of a gun and said, "I'm going to shoot you in the head," then grabbed a bat and followed the three out of the store.

Alsharif told police he was upset because the three wanted to use the bathroom but were not customers.

reviews.text: I had the WORST and the most humiliating experience today at the Target store in Wyomissing PA. I bought a patio umbrella back in June 2008. In about 5 weeks I realized that the product was defective because it would not open all the way and the handle was not easy to operate. I wanted to return the item at the store but because of work I had to travel for the first 3 weeks of August. On Aug 22nd I visited the Wyomissing store and "Lisa" was at the Customer service counter. She was not very happy with my intention to return the umbrella and she asked me to bring the original packaging in case I wanted to return the item. She conveyed this to me in a very rude manner. In any case, I left the store thinking that her rudeness is a one off instance and maybe she was having a bad day. Aug 28th, I go back to the store at 7:45pm with the original receipt and packaging. There were 3 other customers returning items in front of me. "Lisa" was again at the customer service. When I gave her my receipt and told her what the defect was, she started yelling at me and said "It took you all summer to realize that there is a defect" and "You used this all summer and now you want to return it". I tried to explain to her that I am not trying to cheat the system and there is a genuine defect but she singled me out and behaved very rudely in front of other customers. Me and my family ONLY shop at Target, my shopping history will show that I rarely return anything back to the store. But when there is a genuine defect and I bring it to the store within the policy period why am I treated differently. The end result, I brought the defective item back home because I felt humiliated in front of other customers. I am mentally disturbed by this behaviour. Me and my family will never ever shop again at TARGET after this experience and you just lost a loyal customer. $60 dosen't mean anything to me but the amount of humiliation and false accusation that I had to go through for something that is inline with the policy is just ridiculous and unacceptable. I am not sure if this is Lisa's  problem or if this is the company policy to single people out on certain characteristics and humiliate them. I would like this email to be forwarded to the right authorities because they need to know what really goes on in some of their stores and how loyal customers are treated.

reviews.text: I will NEVER set foot in a Target again. I went there to buy what would be my second GPS from them. I was also looking for a gift bag for my sons birthday gift. I must have Batman on it. To my delight, I found a really nice one for only $2.89, but no GPS I liked. While I was at it I picked up 2 toy cars at $5.99 each for my other son and paid with my Target card. So there, I had 3 items. I went home to hide the gift bag until Tuesday and looked at the receipt. Oddly, the items were not named correctly on the receipt. I was charged $6.99 and $5.99 twice. $4 is a lot to overpay for an item, so I went back to fix it. They gave me the runaround for 15 mins asking if I was sure I didnt get something else. I kept saying no and asking if they could explain why the names of the items were weird on the receipt. I had not heard what the security guard had to do with it, but he was shown something on the receipt and went off to do something. I was losing my patience after waiting more than 5 minutes. All they had to do was adjust it. I was furious when the guard returned and walked up to me and said he was looking at the tapes to see what I put in my bag. He said he had footage of me walking away but he could not see what I had. He told the rep to go ahead and refund me the difference. The cashier was very rude to me. Wtf?! You think I stole something, then returned the next day to get a partial $4 refund?? I was so infuriated. Just...wow. I will never set foot in Target again. I am only one customer, but  I get it. I think they treated me that way because I am black. I am not done yet Target. Glad Walmart is across the street.

reviews.text:
On Friday, October 17th, my wife and I went to Target store in Largo, MD (Store#1006) to buy a Baby crib for our unborn child. 

We initially went to the Brandywine location where we spend about $400 on other baby stuff but they did not have the crib we were looking for so we were told that Largo had it in stock.

Upon arrival at Largo store, we were told that a store rep was going to bring the crib we are looking for from an outside truck. 

We waited for 30 minutes and asked for updates and we were told that it will be coming out soon.

After waiting for over an hour, with my pregnant wife on her feet all that time, one of the store reps asked for the status again and we were told that it was too dark and for that matter they are not able to retrieve the item after dark so we should come the next day.

We asked to speak to a manager but instead he or she sent us one of the team leads working called, Winnie who came to confirm that they were not going to get the crib so we should come the next day.

This was a horrible experience as we could have been told earlier that we should go and come the next day and not have us wait for over an hour.

I will never again shop at Target again and I want to return all the things I purchased at the Brandywine store. If you don't care about a pregnant woman being on her feet for over an hour waiting for a crib, you should not care about her money.
Great customer service and everyday priced items.
It's ok needs better customer service
What a joke

The store gets 2 stars just for being Target but the staff in this store is abysmal. Sale items regularly scan at the incorrect price and the staff will spend time haggling with you instead of correcting the price. For example, I went to buy discounted Christmas items and picked up a pack of Thank You Christmas cards from the christmas clearance section. The item rang up at full price even though it was clearly a Christmas item from the clearance section. Instead of adjusting the price they said that many items in the clearance section were not on sale and told me that the cards were full price. The same thing happened on Black Friday. I went to purchase a Memory Game. The paper ad had a sampling of 3 character variations, but there were many more character variations in the Black Friday Memory Game display. The game I picked up from the Black Friday display rang up at full price even though it was a clearly advertised item. Instead of making a quick adjustment the staff made a big deal of removing all the other boxes of the game I had from the Black Friday display (but leaving the 10 other variations that were not in the paper) and telling me that I was getting a deal because it was a mistake. I cross my fingers whenever I go in this store that the item will ring up as advertised so that I will not have wasted my time picking through items.

reviews.text: Probably my favorite Wholefoods in the Boston area. They have so many pre-made options for breakfast, lunch and dinner. Their baked goods are amazing (the croissants are a must). The staff make a good latte, probably the best on Cambridge St. One of the better lunch (albeit more expensive) options in the MGH area.

Besides being jostled by the customers who clearly believe the place to be their own personal pantry and have no consideration for others, one receives even more attitude from the employees! I only went as far to say "Excuse me" to one walking by to be literally brushed off. reviews.text: Can't beat The Standard for something at once hip/modern and comfortable. Sure, the common areas are a bit of a party, and it can be expensive, but, it's New York.

Great location in the Meatpacking District. Very hip, and if you are into the scene then this is the hotel to be in. A piece of advice: if you want a quiet room, do not ask for higher floor count as I unwittingly did one time. There's a nightclub on the rooftop, and I got four-on-the-floor all night. Otherwise it's a decent hotel with modern rooms. The elevators are lame. They're slow and get super congested during rush hours.

You don't get much cooler thank The Standard - great restaurants, beautiful rooms, a biergarten and one of the hardest nightclubs to get into - plus you get to ride in the infamous JayZ/Beyonce/Solange "billion dollars" elevator.

Great place to bring a date, especially when there is a live band.  The decor is phenomenal and the view is spectacular!  You feel like you have stepped into a James Bond movie upon entering the rooftop bar. Haven't stayed at the hotel, but the rooftop bar is a truly remarkable place to enjoy some live music.

Nice bars at the top of the hotel with great music and attentive bartenders.. lobby entrance seems vast and deserted set way back on 10th/11th Avenue south of 14th st in Meatpacking.  Restaurant at the bottom has decent food and ambiance but not as fun as the top floors.  Trendy hotel fun for probably one night in downtown west nyc.

reviews.text: Found good deals & food specialties not found in other supermarkets. Was there late in the evening & staff was very helpful!

I shop at the Super Wal-Mart in Bechtelsville all the time.  It is my main grocery store.  I go there because you can't beat the prices.  But I am so annoyed because this Wal-Mart has a serious problem with their carts.  I would say most of them make a clunk clunk clunking noise when you push them.  Every week I go there, I pull out a cart and start to push it, and it starts clunking.  I try two or three in a row that all do the same thing.  When I'm shopping, I hear other shoppers with their carts making that loud noise too.  It is embarrassing to walk around with a cart making such a noise, and trying out two to three carts looking for one that doesn't make that sound.  This has been going on there for years.  I even told one of the men at the front door that "this cart is bad" and I thought he would make sure it didn't get put in with all the others again, but he put it right back in with the others.  I am so annoyed that I wish I could justify shopping at a more expensive grocery store.

I remember when this store first opened, it was a nightmare! every single cashier had their service light blinking, the customer service desk were clueless about returns and kept bumping us all over to do a return. The damn manager was doing gawd knows what in his/her office and never bothered to come out to get everything under control.

1) Their stock is NEVER up to date, even if you search for it on their website and still says in stock and you go and its not there.

2) I had so many rude encounters there like as soon as I had all my items on the counter, a cashier said shes leaving and flicked the light off. RUDE! another time for Christmas 2007, the greeter started to yell loud for me to see my receipt for items that weren't in bags. She did it very, very rudely. I gave a look to my fiancee and another worker seen that and had the nerve to tell me that they have to do that. Well, you didn't have to get half the stores attention doing it!!

3) Items are NEVER in stock. You go back a week later and the shelf is still bare. B) When you ask for someone to see if an item is in stock in the back, you wait 30 mins for some lazy worker to come and tell you they don't have any left, which you know is crock.

4) When you call customer service and they direct you to a department that when someone is supposed to be there and it rings and rings and you have to go to Walmart and figure it out yourself, and they use the talkie to see whats going on and on the other end some cranky old bat answers in a abrupt, quick way to say no its not here or something like that. Pick up the phone next time!

5) You can never find anyone in most departments to help you, if you ask someone thats in that dept, they don't even try to pretend to care, just give you a flat look like your bothering them.

I don't even bother going back to this store anymore. Save your time and go somewhere else! A lot of people there are incompetent, rude, and don't care.

reviews.text:
I am a customer of Walgreens Pharmacy located on JFK in Philadelphia. I am writing a formal complaint in reference to several recent encounters with Purvi Vyas (Pharmacy Manager) I've experienced while visiting Walgreens the past few months. Most recently I went in the pharmacy on Monday, April 20, 2015 at 5:00pm to have a prescription filled. I was asked for my ID and told there would be a wait. My response to the wait was I would pick up my medication on Tuesday April 21, 2015 on my lunch as I work across the street. I was also informed they would hold on to my ID.  I informed the staff holding on to my ID would not work considering carrying photo ID is the law. I was given a hard time about getting my ID back. Usually they simply scan it in the system. I was also informed they would not be able to fill one of my scripts because they did not have the medication in stock. My response to them not having the medication was "you normally order the meds".  I was told they could not order the meds and instructed to take the script elsewhere. On Tuesday April 21, 2015 at 12:30 I went to the pharmacy to pick up my medication and I am asked for ID. The gentleman scanned the ID and gave it  back to me as they normally do however the day before it was not that simple. I was informed there was an hour wait. I explained it has been almost 24hours the script should be filled.  The gentleman stated he apologized but he'd have it in an hour. In the meantime the gentleman asked "what about the other meds we normally fill for you". I informed him of my experience the day before when I was told they were unable to fill the prescription, the gentleman stated he would order the medication if it's not in stock. I told him I'd be back after 5pm on April 21, 2015. At 3:30 I received a call from my doctors office stating the pharmacy called the office asking questions which violate HIPPA policy.  I was informed the pharmacy asked questions regarding my treatment, questions beyond verifying the scripts.  The pharmacy never provided the doctors office any release of information authorization signed by myself. I called the pharmacy immediately to complain and was told they were only doing their job.  I went to pick up the medication and the pharmacist refused to fill the script stating she needs to verify the medication with the doctor who wrote the script and only the doctor who wrote the script.  The office I attend is a practice of several doctors, I never see the same doctor as they all have different schedules.  I explained this to the pharmacist and she refused. Any doctor in the office can verify treatment as they work as a team. I've notice how this pharmacist profiles people when they come in. I've often heard her make comments about customers. She's refused to fill my meds in the past stating since she filled my script two days later she would not fill the new script until an additional two days later. She fills medication at her own discretion which is unethical.  I use Walgreens as the location is conveniently across the street from my full time job and 3 blocks from my part time job. The pharmacy is located above suburban station which is also the location of where I catch my train to and from work.  I feel that this is a matter that needs attention bought to it. I do plan on speaking with an attorney regarding the matter as I feel I have been treated unfairly.  I asked for corporate information and was informed "the only info they could give was that particular stores information and being as though she (Purvi Vyas) was the pharmacy manager there was no one else I could speak with".   The stores information is as follows:
 
Walgreen Co
 Store #07336
 1617 John F. Kennedy Blvd
 Philadelphia, PA19103
 215-561-1316
Convenient and they have just about everything you'd expect. I just wish the store, including the pharmacy, were open 24 hrs. I don't think they realize how many people are living around them.

reviews.text: The Columbus/Mitchell's Fish Market is a great place at a decent price. I took my wife here for her birthday this year. It was a Wednesday and we arrived around 6pm without a reservation and were seated immediately. By about 7pm, it felt much more crowded, but there were still a few tables available. We each ordered a specialty martini and shared an appetizer of mussels. For dinner she had the chef special which was cod stuffed with lobster and I had the Shang Hai sytled salmon with shrimp and scallops. If you like an asian-sesame flavored fish dish - I would recommend it. Being that it was her birthday, our waitress informed me they do not sing, but we were offered a free dessert. Our bill was under $100 which is reasonable for the quality of service and fare. This place seems like a great option for hosting business luncheons and dinners.
very good wasn't disappointed

Among the best seafood restaurants in town, with excellent selections, and wonderful service. Consistent in how well they prepare and present whatever you order. It is a delight to be there!

reviews.text:
I met with Marek after I saw my car online.  He was extremely helpful with the whole buying experience.  Of course, the day after I gave the check over for purchase with "as is, no warranty"-a dashboard light comes on!  

I contacted Marek and he sent me to their service department.  Mark, Hannah, and Jitterbug made my service experience easy..fixing what needed to be fixed for free.  No hassle, no questions.

I love the car and really appreciate the service I received--I anticipate going back for servicing needs in the future.

We bought a car about 4 -5 years ago from George at the Edgewood us 1 car lot  and when we needed another one we went right back with the same awesome attention & experience from him, buying a car from them is so easy and laid back. Our next vehicle that we buy will be from Tillman and our sales person will be George.

Marek at Tillman made my car buying experience a breeze! He went over and above to make sure I got the car that I wanted and that it was a great deal. There was no pressure or stress, but he stayed on top of the details through the whole process. I would highly recommend Tillman and Marek to anyone looking to buy a car!

My experience at Tillman Automotive was the best! I never thought I would be able to purchase a vehicle without a cosigner and they made it happen with an affordable monthly payment. My salesman was OG and he was the best. We did everything over the phone because of my work schedule.  When I was able to get off , he made sure the vehicle was still available.  I took the 2013 Chevy Captiva for a test drive and loved it. Thank you OG for all of your help. I would recommend you to go to Tillman Auto on main street and tell OG I sent you. 25yrs of experience and No pressure 😃

My wife and I were looking for lightly used van with low miles, and found a 2014 Town and Country online at Tillman Auto.  Although we live in Mandarin and had never previously considered going downtown to buy a car, we decided to take a chance as the vehicle appeared to be just what we were looking for.  We're glad we did.  The van was nice, as was our salesman, Marek.  We got a good price, when compared to vans that were available at larger dealerships, making it worth the drive.  A few months later, we had a minor issue with the van that we expected to be covered by the manufacturer's warranty, but it wasn't.  The Chrysler dealer wanted to charge us around $600 for what we considered a minor repair.  We decided to call Tillman since we'd had the van only a short time and thought that this was something that should have been fixed when the van was reconditioned to sell it.  We dealt with Marek again, and we're so pleased to advise that Tillman made the repairs at no cost to us.  No questions asked.  I've bought a lot of cars over the years, and you don't find a lot of honest folks in the car business.  We believe Tillman is a rare place that can be trusted.  Thanks Tillman and Marek.

reviews.text:
Target has an unpublished return policy, which is unethical, and highly suspect. They also practice a frustrating policy of placing a firewall between every level of authority, making any attempt to find a resolution to any issue virtually impossible. 

Ask for a supervisor - You might be successful in there in fact being one available, but if arriving at a solution requires a manager

Asking for a manager - If this person is on sight then you're extremely lucky, but if they're not, or they are unable to assist in a resolution, you're left to ask the question(s)
'Who is the .... ' and 'How do I contact them?'

This is where you enter the world of 'screw the customer completely'. You get a first name only, which is of no practical use, given you will be refused any further information, such as; a last name, phone number(s), email address, or even an address for an office to send - yes, a letter. You will be directed to the customer relations number, however, they too will refuse to provide you with anything more than email, which is - wait for it - a generic customer relations email dump. Call corporate and it's a mirror of the toll free number.  Ask for a supervisor on any of the customer relation numbers and the damn process begins again.

It's a Target middle finger to your concern.

I am completely disgusted with Target and the customer service that Newport News VA Target store has to offer. I will never shop here again. I will let my friends and family know everything and hopefully they lose more customers. I got paid on Friday  December 13th, 2013. Since that pay day I have not been paid yet. When I call the store, I get crappy customer service and I'm left to feel like I am wrong for calling about MY check that I worked hard for. I try to call corparate and any number associated with Target and all you get is a dialtone. Yes I have quit Target and I will never work there again. Nor will I shop, drive by, or look at the store again. I hate Target and the Newport News Target Store managers.
They are open until eleven pm but would be nice to have one that stayed open until midnight of a 24 hour store !!!

The experience was interesting since the food was a cold/hot prepared take out/eat in lunch that when weighed in on their deli scale and 2 registers at 4 different weights and subsequent prices. To Whom It May Concern:
I wanted to write and thank the staff  at my local Target Pharmacy in Daphne, Alabama.  Yesterday, 2/8/14, I showed up at the pharmacy a few minutes after 5pm.  They were closing down for the day, which I was unaware of, but the manager, Marie and the pharmacist agreed to fill my Rx.  They could have easily sent me away, but they  were generous with their time and stayed to help a mom who desperately needed some medicine for a sick child.  Unfortunately, several problems arose due to my child being a new patient, with new insurance.  But they never gave up.  And my child received a much need night of rest.  I wish I had thought to get the young mans name that worked so hard to get this filled, because I would surely like to recognize him personally.  I know working in the service industry can be an often thankless job, so I just want to say thank you to both of them for going above and beyond the normal protocol.  
Sincerely,
Julie Pitts

I went to purchase a crib & mattress along with many other baby items for my daughter.  I spent over $700 while shopping there.  The only reason I went is that the baby gift registry was at Target.  I can assure you I will not be returning to that store.

The register area manager was incredibly rude when I was at the register attempting to purchase the crib & mattress.  How was I supposed to know that I needed to actually bring the crib & mattress to the register? Exactly how was I going to fit the two large items in my shopping cart?  Her answer was "Well lets see, maybe you ask for help".  I then told her well maybe you should put a sign up explaining the process by the crib area.

I then had to walk around the store to look for someone to help me.

If I could have found the same crib in any other store I would have told her to shove it up her ass.  

Target you have lost a customer for life.

I would like to give good customer feed back, but in this case is not an option. Today, on my birthday. My family wanted to purchase me a grill. As we shop , my family saw a grill that it was on our budget... Char-Broil® Infrared 3 Burner Gas Grill with Cabinets ... It was advertise with signs for $199.99, ( i took a photo of the display). I requested for a target employee to come and help us out. Employee ( Carolina) working near or in the department called another  employee ( Tobby) . They both confirmed the price of the grill. We were a bit skeptical. So we question the employee.. and ( Carolina) assure us that they would honor the price on the item. They check the backroom, they both came back.. "They don't have anymore"  the employee assure us that they will honor the price.. So i check online for the item Char-Broil® Infrared 3 Burner Gas Grill with Cabinets ( 	Online Item #: 14275091  ) . It said $349.99..

SO we decide to go another Target.. So we went to the Kendall Drive..15005 SW 88th St, Miami, FL 33196.. The Manager ( Veronica) was helpful, She called the one in Cutler Ridge. and spoke to a manager ( Andres ) he confirmed they had two in the back.... 

Again we drove back to the Cutler Ridge Target , We were under the impression that they would honor the price.. $199.99.

When we get their, the Manager ( Andres) did not honor the price given to us by the original employees.. 

His response was..." She's not a SALARY EMPLOYEE" , I was upset, now customer have to walk around store asking if employees are salary..

I told the manager that no matter if an employee is salary of hour, that She represented Target..  He was a bit rude.. He offered a 20% discount ..

That was not acceptable to us.. my family spent almost 2 hours running between store.. And Target should honor that price..

We shop in Target.. Your Signs say : Expect more, Pay Less"    

we expect more- instead we received nothing but disappointment... Not a way to go home , without my birthday gift...

Thank you...
Great customer service

I have never written a review about anything , this is my first one.
But I had to comment on the way one of the young cahiers wore his pants. His shirt was trying to cover the way his pants hung down below his butt, it looked so not Target like. I love this store That kind of attire should not be allowed.
Thanks and I hope its corrected but more than that I hope its not allowed.

reviews.text: I've had it with this target. I'm 9 months pregnant and completely exhausted. I went in wed and wanted to use the carts.. my feet were swollen and I was really exhausted.. none worked. reviews.text: Poor customer service.

4/8/2010 I went to this Target looking for a specific Laundry detergent for a friend who was moving. I couldn't find the brand/type & tried one of those red phones. Nothing happened. I finally saw someone walking my way (no name tag) in a red shirt so I asked if she worked there & told her what I was looking for. She looked around & said "Well I don't see it...". Then a man came out form "the back" & asked if he could help. She tried to relay what it was I was looking for (I had to correct her) & he said that the non bleach alternatives were sometimes "over here". They were far enough away from me that I could no longer see them, so I was trying to follow their voices. They made some comments I couldn't heAR & were laughing & just left the area. My friend (I called her cell) said she did get it there but there was a Walmart even closer to her house that would also have it. I NEVER thought I'd be saying I got better service at Walmart than Target but I did.

reviews.text: The customer service representatives were absolute crap when I went here last year. After we were ready to check out, the associate rang up a bunch of the next customer's items and charged me for them!  He says "oh, well you just bought that guy's stuff."  He looks at the customer behind us and asks, "do you want him to just buy your stuff?"  What?  Why would I want to buy a stranger's items for them??

reviews.text: Target has lost my business forever.  I purchased an Xbox One from this location on 12/11/2014. The boxing looked a little worn, but I was anxious to play and didn't think it was a big deal. Upon starting my Xbox I entered the Destiny game I had just bought an noticed the Xbox was having trouble taking the disk. With a little push the disk went in, however the Xbox could not read the game.  I tried 3 more times, same thing. I also tried a few DVDs and the Xbox would not take, read or return the disks cleanly.  Ok, broken unit, i'll go back to Target and exchange it.  When i tried to return it, it turns out the serial number on the box/receipt does not match the serial of the unit and no return can be processed.  I believe this unit was returned once before, due to the questionable boxing and unmatching serial numbers and the employees at this store did not catch it the first time.  Now i have to pay the price and figure out how to repair this device or return it to Microsoft.  I have a steady job, make good money and have no reason to try and "cheat" target.  As i said, all of my business and my wife's business will no longer go to target. That is thousands of dollars over many decades that you will now never get, over a $350 Xbox.

This is the WORST Target I've ever been into. It's a total mess,  half the shelves are empty,  they're nearly out of toys.  Employees were standing around talking and eating and not a single one even looked at me much less offer to help me find anything. Not a typical Target experience. They need a visit from corporate or something,  soon.

My daughter and I searched high and low for an iPhone 5 in gold, which she'd earned for doing so well in school. Finally, we tracked one down at the Target in Norcross. They associate was so helpful and thoroughly explained the insurance plan, which we bought (and usually don't buy). I love a store where the associates come to work prepared to...well, work.

Purchased an on sale item, the associate rang it up as full price...walked directly back in, waited for an associate to come to the return counter for 5 minutes... Then when I finally asked someone, she came and told me the item was not on sale (even though it was an end cap promo). She told me the sign was old (even though it was still up) and that each store ran different promotions (because I had purchase the same sheets the night before at a store less than 5 Miles away), and rudely returned my money. WASTE of time....
I am indifferent towards the lack of service there.  I am just going to shop somewhere else.

reviews.text: Worst target ever. Customer service is just the icing on the cake of how horrible target is.

On March 1, 2014 purchased Earth's Best Baby Food Pouch - Pear Carrot Apricot 4.2oz for my son. I normally check the expiration before I buy, but didn't this time. The date of expiration was February 4, 2014. I called the store and they said they were pulling the expired food now that they are aware of it. I also requested that another non-expired pouch be waiting for me when I return the expired one.

When I went to return the expired food, there was nothing waiting for me. The gentlemen behind the counter couldn't get in contact with the manager or infant department, so I retrieved the new item myself and returned to the counter before anyone was there to assist me. The entire point me of requesting it be waiting is to not waste more of my time.

Next I went to the Target site to say how I was unhappy about the selling of expired baby food and the return process when the target form refused my submission because it stated it wasn't a produce name. I tried Earth's Best Baby Food Pouch - Pear Carrot Apricot, Earth's Best Baby Food Pouch, Earth's Best and Target. When I put in Target it gave me a 404 Error and wiped out my data.

I then called the 800 number, the first time I was hung up on. Then when I did get someone his English is barley understandable. He then transferred me to the 'grocery' department where I was on hold for about 3-4 minutes when I hung up.

I am disappointed at the over all experience of this Target and the IT department who runs the website. It is no wonder they were hacked if they can't even get the email submission portion to work.

Needs a self-checkout line.
Also, why did Target buy credit card machines capable of chip and pin/chip and signature but not actually use them? You can use your chip at Walmart...

reviews.text: My recent visit to this Target was absolutely unacceptable and insulting. After being told that there were three of an item being sent to this store I came to the store early to wait in line for its release. I managed to be third in line, just barely making the cut. An employee came up to the group of us waiting in front of the store and stated once again that there were only three systems available. The store opened and we happily walked to the electronics section where we were informed that they only had one system available. After a number of us obviously disgruntled customers asked them to search for the full three systems guaranteed to us by multiple employees over the phone and in person they manage to scrounge up a second system from some mysterious backroom. I attempted to explain my frustration to them and offered them a solution that at least would cool my frustration, calling the long gone employee that had come to us and told us about the three systems to ask him if he misplaced a system or had simply been incorrect. That was all I wanted, some explanation for the lies. Instead they attempted to buy me off with a cheap 3 dollar apology gift card which in 20-god-damn-15 obviously buys nothing of value and is only a pathetic attempt to get me to buy something else that I did not wait in line since 6 in the morning for but with the equivalent of a pack of gum knocked off the price tag. After a minute or two of asking to speak to higher management or for the man in front of me to call this employee for some simple answers during which I never once raised my voice I was told that they were going to have someone escort me out of the building if I didn't buy something right then. I finally gave up, too utterly insulted and mistreated by the smug electronics manager and the other employee near him to stand to be in their presence for a single second longer. I left, and my blood is still boiling as I type this. I will never come back to this target. I would suggest that anyone reading this not go to this target but I know that obviously this will have little to no effect on your consideration. No one will read this, and in all honesty my situation was probably a unique occurrence. 99.9% of everyone that has ever been alive to visit a target and done so went in, grabbed what they needed, perhaps some even  asked an employee where something was located, then left. But if you are EVER required to go to a target in ANY context that will require you to deal with these people for any longer than a few minutes I have to say avoid this place like the plague. They do not respond well to reasonable requests that go beyond typing in an item number into the computer and you leave with a beyond sour taste in your mouth.

reviews.text: It was clean, and th e employees were very friendly. I really enjoyed shopping there, even browsing around.

I almost always enjoy shopping at Target, however I've never experienced such consistently bad customer service as I have at this particular Target store. On several occasions I've come upon a cashier checking his or her cell phone as well as employees texting and taking personal calls AT THE REGISTER with customers in line. I've also been completely ignored by a cashier for several minutes while he talked on the phone, then instead of ending his call to do his job, he actually continued talking while completing my purchase. 
On another occasion, weeks later, I came to a register where a different employee was checking his text messages at the register and after acknowledging me through the piece of gum that was hanging out of his mouth, reluctantly checked out my items.
I've also experienced rude and unhelpful "service" at the return counter while attempting to return and exchange items from my bridal registry. 
I'm not sure who is managing the Timber Drive store in Garner, but I've worked retail for many years and can't imagine why these practices are being tolerated. I'm certain, this is isn't behavior that's consistent with the corporate standard.
I've shopped at Target stores throughout the Triangle and in various states and will continue to do so, but the store at 2700 Timber Drive in Garner will no longer receive my family's business.

reviews.text: This is by far the worst Target store I have ever been to, and I shop at Target very often. Shopped at this location twice this week, and in the two times I experienced the same problems. It is no coincidence when it happens twice. The staff were not very friendly. The advertised prices did not ring up correct, the coupons will not go through, although for the exact product indicated. They had a unilever special where if you buy 4 products, you'll get a $5 gift card. It was advertised in the Sunday paper, the Target ad of this week and on the shelves under each of the items I picked up. Yet I get to the register and the special doesn't ring up. When I told the cashier, she seemed oblivious to what's in the ad. I asked her to look in the ad, she refused and insisted on getting someone to look where the items were??? The manager when she came, seemed to be unaware of the special as well. She scanned each item individually to make sure I am not making it up. Of course I was right, the gift card was suppose to come up automatically, it did NOT. The same thing happened with another special that was advertised on the shelf, I read the details when I picked up the items, it was buy 3 get one free, I made sure to pick up the sizes indicated in the flyer on the shelf. It also didn't ring up right, this time I wanted them to go and check , but the line was held up for a long time already. It was very embarrassing. Gave the cashier my coupons, and started looking for my card to pay. She scanned them, (or pretended to do so) I noticed one of them didn't come up on the screen, I told her that it didn't go through, it was for a free item and she needed to enter the price, she said, "no, it did go through" . She lied, because I looked at the receipt and couldn't find it. By the time I finally finished checking out I was late to my appointment, and ended up paying almost twice as I though I will. I wanted to take all of this stuff back, but with the way they work I didn't sweat it. I WILL NOT be shopping there again.

We were at the store getting a couple of things. I paid in cash and laid the cash on the counter and was digging around for change. I found some looked up and my money was gone and the casheir had his hand in his pocket and wouldn't take it out. So I had to pay again but it was pretty clear that he stole my money because he wouldn't take his hand out of his pocket. I will never go back there. They need to hire honest, trusting people. But it was just that store otherwise Target is OK just not that one.
