reviews.text:
Absolutely amazing!! 
This is the most absurd thing I have ever been a part of. I am wondering exactly why it is that I was convinced to get a Red Card for free shipping and to save 5% online when I, in fact, can't use it!! 

The account is set up to draft directly from my bank - which has money in it. I am sure that this will fall on DEAF ears since this will be the 5th time that I have tried to make an effort to GIVE you nearly $1500!!! 
Never in my life have I had an issue so devoid of common sense. My bank has money. You have a product I want. I want to give you my money for the product. And, even though I can use my debit card to buy plane tickets, cruises, cameras or even music. For some reason Target has to lock down my card so that I can't purchase the items I'd like. 

And, I understand that Target wants to have more smaller purchases to "track" and to "build" a trend to "validate" that I have money to make a purchase. Whereas, in reality, I know that you just want to make sure that I buy a lot of things from you. Well, I haven't. I haven't not because I didn't want to but because I hadn't looked. And now, my wife has looked. She has found some things that she would like. And since I haven't bought enough from you using my card of "high enough dollar" I can't buy $1486 worth of things from you. 

It is absurd. And, all it has done is moved me more to Amazon where they like money, and take my money. And, I'm okay with that. 

Thanks for not helping. I can't believe that you can't run the card, ask for a check, offer another method of payment with similar discounts (5% off and free shipping). What is exactly the benefit of the Red Card, other than annoying me to the point that you are losing a customer? I guess though for a multi-million dollar company my little sale means nothing. 

The problem with our country isn't sending jobs away. It's losing our sense of customer service. It's the last true product that we have. I wasn't offered a solution of any kind. I was only told NO. In fact, I was told I was declined - a phrase used for CREDIT, not DEBIT!

-Dan

reviews.text:
I went there today (fri. 11/21/14 at 5:30pm) to buy chewing tobacco and gas up with my Frys VIP card to save .10 cent per gallon. First, he tried to sell me tobacco that expired in early october. I thought, that was an honest mistake. 

But when I gassed up at $2.69 a gallon with .10 cents off per gallon, I noticed the reciept said $2.67 per gallon. I asked the clerk why it only took .02 cent off, he said "because we charge .08 cent per gallon when you use a debit or credit card." I asked, "Are you the owner?" He said he just works there. I asked if I could have his number to talk to him about this and he then said he was the manager but that's the way it was.

I will never go there again and will report them to the Frys Company, BBB and Consumer Affairs about this. I think they are cheating people in more ways than one.

I have been outside now for over 15 minutes. I need gas. Car will not start now and you have a sign on the door that says back in 5. I only have cash. This is ridiculous. When I walk inside I bet your store looks like crap and is run badly. What the hell?
So there's a $1 fee for using my debit plus my gas price was 8 cents higher than if I would pay cash?? Really!!
Do not go here.  Everytime I visit this location I get people asking me for money or to buy something from them.
The station is very run down...I went to 2 pumps before I could get one to work. The screens were unreadable.

reviews.text: I have shopped almost exclusively at this location for over six months now.  The only benefit to shopping at this store is that it is open 24/7 and within a mile to my home... the only reason I will use them at all in the future though I will be trying to get to Trader Joe's, Whole Foods, or any other available market like the Super Walmart only a couple of miles away.  The reasons for this are simple.  *** Smith's routinely cannot honor a sale prices advertised in their own throw away paper.  Usually, the excuse is because it it not marked as such i.e. chicken advertised at .99 a lbs.  But, since their meat department didn't make any notation on any of the labels noting the mark down the register personnel refused me several times to honor the price... even when they knew the chicken was on sale.  Because according to them - the department is responsible.  They kindly offered to charge me "full price" though.  *** Just today Smith's electronic scales were non-operational and again a trip to the store for naught as they could not honor their sales prices as advertised but, again kindly offered to charge me full price... today they generously offered to have me comeback with my receipt and "work it out" for me later.  ... REALLY?  ... and finally, they are rather poorly stocked in several areas that I prefer like fine cheeses, good wine, cooking sherry, etc...   Looks like I am going to be going to Trader Joe's and even Whole Foods more often.

This store like all Smiths is super clean,It has lots of $1.00 specials(10 for 10) up front convenient to stock up when you first arrive.The meat is High quality as is the produce.    The sales on meat are great! The checkers get you in and out in no time. It is definitely high end shopping for North Las Vegas  with lower prices......In Summerlin all the wealthy celebrities go to Smiths.Use your reward card and save BIG BUCKS on gas.
Smiths are always a great place to shop. They are always clean and knowledgeable. They r pricier thsn ur Wal-Mart or other stores but they make up for it w service.

reviews.text: Walmart in general is a terrible outfit, this particular Walmart is great at sweeping things under the rug. We've had problems with purchasing their "always fresh" produce, only to have it rot within a couple days. The Assistant Manager in the auto department doesn't like to give all options for oil changes, just the most expensive one. Long lines at the registers, they used to call up all cashiers when line were out into the isles, not anymore. And the Pharmacy is extremely slow, long lines and very understaffed. Then you have the cashiers, some are very nice, there are some working there that treat you like you are an inconvenience. No greeting, talking with you, very cold. I really do not like this Walmart.

I came here with a friend and waited for two hours to get meds for her daughter after being told repeatedly it would be 10-15 minutes longer. Then they closed for lunch knowing that we were still waiting. We won't go back here as they clearly don't care about their customers.

Must say, this wal-mart has a lot of stuff and is a nice central location for various things.

As another reviewer stated, the lines have been long as of lately and as i've only been using this location for about 4 months, it's been a constant like that for about.... 4 months.

Suggestion... Don't decide to go at 1-am because there will be less people... true, but there's also that many less cashiers, still a long wait if you have more than 3 items.
Its a very nice place

Pharmacy waiting is TERRIBLE.  Auto/oil/tire waiting is TERRIBLE.  I have few other options for some of the grocery items, so I have to go here sometimes.  I've since switched my pharmacy to Family Fresh (not much better, but only 2 options in town), and take my oil changes to Express Lube (EXCELLENT).  I have actually called the management from my phone from 5 carts deep waiting in line to request additional cashiers.  What's worse is the employees have to bear the brunt of disgruntled customers when it's clearly a staffing and management issue.  Mind you, this has not been going on as of recently, it's been going on here for YEARS...at least 3 years...as long as I've lived on that end of town anyway.

Shopper beware if you have a schedule to keep!!

When they get home, it takes them a couple of days to get over it. I don't want them to hurry, but....In their defense though, it was during the holidays, and they were short of groomers. Otherwise, I love the groomers, especially Jamie, and the people are friendly.

When ever I come here, they ALWAYS have at least one dead fish in their tank. It's disgusting, my friend has complained to them numerous times. I no longer shop at Petco anymore, and make the drive to Petsmart. I also hate how Petco FORCES hermit crabs to live in toxic painted shells just to make a few extra bucks.

Groom Salon needs more customer service training!!! I called and schedule an appointment for a hair cut for my Lhasa Apse female on 1/30/2014 for 2/2/2014 but they made the appointment for 3/2/2014 instead. When I showed up for my 10:00am appointment on 2/2/2014 I was told that I was not on the scheduled and the groomer was all booked for the day. Who claimed to be the manager at the groom salon was very unprofessional and did not take responsibility of her associates mistake. I did not get an apology after all, I had a terrible customer service experiece!!!! I do not recomend this place for grooming.

Friendly Staff. We took our high strung puppies to get their toe-nails clipped and the staff did great with them. One hint though.  If its your 1st time, make sure you bring your animals immunizations records. They will not be able to take care of your best friends needs without them. :)  Also watch for deals on toys etc.  We all know that keeping our pets happy can get a little spendy.

reviews.text: Stayed here on the weekend of May 17-19 of 2013 for the American Triple-T. I needed a hotel that would let me bring my dog. For an extra $10/night I was able to bring my best pal Ichiban. The hotel room was average but for the price I wasn't expecting much. I would have no problem staying there again. It wasn't the nicest hotel I've ever stayed at, but again, for the price it's the compromise you make. It was reasonably close to my race venue and nearby the town's center, food, and CVS. Oh, and there's a pool which was a nice surprise, even though I didn't use it.

i was strapped for cash and was very pleased with the prices... however, i was very displeased with the condition and smell of the room.  Granted, i knew being in a smoking room, i shouldnt expect it to be too fresh but the smell was more of a wet carpet or some type of mold smell. clearly the smell was coming from the stiff stle carpet.  i also was not satified with the bathroom, besides the the dropplets of urine left on the seat  and the hair left in the tub i guess the bathroom was in fair condition. I wasnt expecting much but i was expecting at the very least a clean room. i also was over charged by the hotel and have yet to have the funds released into my account. I am very upset with the stay i had espically because it was my first and probably my last time staying at super 8. i believe the prices are the only "good" part of the stay. oh and the front desk woman "angie" was very nice. i mean if only there hotel condition was as bright as the staff... but i guess u get what u pay 4. dont go there. try the comfort inn up the street!

This hotel was very nice considering we had just stopped at a crappy hotel just about a mile back down the road and well we were tired and had been looking for a good place to stay before we continued our trip the next day. The staff was very nice polite. Our room was very clean and tidy and the beds were very comfortable and soft. The bathroom had alot of room to move around and was also very clean. If we're in the area again this will most likely be the place were we stay.

Well its a busy Super 8 thats for sure,the staff is friendly and there seemed to be lots of help around. The rooms are satisfactory, nothing fancy that's for sure. Breakfast was gone by 8:45 when I got there, I mean there was still some crumbs but nothing much left. The internet does NOT work well, but that may have been because everyone was on it. So  I am giving this Super 8  a decent review, not great but not bad either.

The staff does the laundry after midnight and the commercial washer is very loud and vibrates the floor and walls above it making it impossible to sleep. Our non smoking room must have been an afterthought considering the smell of smoke, burn holes in the carpet and on the edge of the sink. The carpet was filthy and has holes in it. Do not stay here, you've been warned.

reviews.text: Don't go there, the service is horrible the younger lady there is snotty and rude, the food is disgusting and sloppy. The tacos are dry, the bread is old and hard as rocks, the steak tastes like dog food, I've watched them water down the sodas and apparently the cooks have never heard of sanitation.

good service but the food does not taste good from the bakery all bread is three days ago. hard as stone
best tacos i've had in the suburbs and they the fresh baked bread is pretty cheap

We're Anglos and we love this place. The salsa is homemade and terrific. The tacos are simple but oh so good, and the right price! They'll make you a plain, avocado taco, although it's not on the menu - try with cilantro and onion or tomato and lettuce. The chorizo is scrumptious. We also enjoy quesadillas, carne asada, and their burritos. You get chips and salsa for free if you eat in, and a tub of pickled carrots, garlic, and jalapeños on your table (may not be your style, but I think it's great stuff). The horchata here is so-so, but they have a cooler full of US and Mexican sodas, including bottles of Starbucks frappacino! They have baked goods as well - great cookies and we love the bolillos - bread stuffed with cream cheese and cooked green pepper. The menu is mostly in Spanish, but the cashier speaks English and can help you find what you want.

reviews.text:
I’m extremely disappointed at the service and treatment my mom received at your pharmacy at 7229 W Oakland Park Blvd, Lauderhill, FL 33313 on 10/21/14. My mom’s doctor sent a prescription to your store and my mom called to inquire. Your tech asked my mom for her insurance card information, my mom gave her the card info but your tech insisted that’s not the number and proceeded to scream at her. (where do they do this?) After all the screaming, my mom asked to your tech her name and she refused to give it. When my mom asked for her supervisor, she hung up on her.

My mom called back and finally got your manager on duty at that time Mohamed. He tried to convince my mom it was a misunderstanding. My mom inquired how is a hang up and a refusal to give a name a misunderstanding. My mom asked if that’s how you treat your customers and would call your corporate number, he said to go ahead. My mom explained she could take her business elsewhere, his exact response was you guys have plenty of other customers and did not need her business.

Needless to say, my mom went back and took bac the prescription and they were reluctant to give it to her. She got her prescription and got it filled without the attitude and rudeness. He and my dad will be transferring all their prescriptions to CVS along with the rest of my family. I made sure to share my experience on my Facebook and the other social media sites to let others know how much you value your customers. Very sad how you guys treat seniors at that store.
Can't reach them by phone.  On hold 35 minutes on two different phones.
No complaints.

The person saying the pharmacy is always "convieniently on lunch break"... Just so you know, it also "conveniently" says on their pull down windows that Target Pharmacy will take their lunch break from 1:30-2PM when there is only one pharmacist on duty. If this happens any other time, it's probably because someone went to the restroom or something. 

With my experiences, they are always punctual. They know my husband and I by name, and always have out auto-fills ready when needed. If I drop off a prescription, they do take about 30min at the most, but that's usually during peak hours. Usually the norm is 15-20 min which is completely reasonable, they do have other things to do, right?

i shopped there the monday before black friday if they didnt have the toy in stock that was on sale they issued rainchecks which i thought was great until i have had to call every day for a month to see if they have them in for a RUDE woman in toys to tell me we dont have them dont know if we are going to get them!  SO i am taking all the video games i bought to go with the vmotions (rain check item) and i will not buy toys from a store whom gives out rainchecks for items they are not going to get in!!  VERY DISAPPOINTED IN TARGET IN FLORENCE KY!!

reviews.text: Being a die-hard harry potter fan when the bluray set came out I immediately called target and put a copy on hold. reviews.text: I wouldn't normally write a review but I just received some excellent service at Walgreens tonight. I went to 2 different Rite Aid stores in Sherman Oaks and Valley Village trying to get passport photos taken. At both stores the photos came out badly. Went to Walgreens to see if they even offer this service. The assistant manager, Angel, said no problem and went to work with a far better camera and printer. He helped me adjust the photos when needed and they came out beautifully. Then to top it off, right at the end he also gave me a great discount. Top quality service!

the pharmacy is a joke during the day. never answer their phone. one time I was on hold for 2 hours and drove there while on hold. the lady was eating burger king sitting on the counter. So I waited one more hour as I watched the line behind me pile up in the drive up window. Finally the lazy girl got off her butt to serve me. I asked her why she never picked up the phone. she said did not get paid enough for that.

I give this Walgreens my same rating as I've given any other - lousy customer service.  The Pharmacy never seems to have even the most commonly-prescribed medications, and the 'standard' answer is 'It take a week to get it!' - when most 'mom and pop' pharmacies have the same the next day (most of these smaller pharmacies also deliver prescriptions - something you'll NEVER encounter in ANY Walgreens!); for the most part, the drive-through windows are inefficent - it can take twenty minutes or longer just to get service at some (and, for the most part, these staffers are the rudest you'll ever encounter) - if Walgreens is going to offer these, then at least adequately staff them (with staff trained in customer service!).  Walgreens has gotten much too large to care about its customers; few staffers will ever know you by name, most have many different Pharmacists on duty so the customer never knows any by name - consequently, I've come to the conclusion I'll not be using ANY Walgreens no matter how closeby they might be.
Love it!

Never mind they cant find your prescription, THAT THEY MAKE THE DOCTOR PHONE OVER AND OVER LIKE IN SOME THREE STOOGES ROUTINE !  They are clueless and as lazy as they come. It's like talking to 5 Alzheimer victims who are locked in isolation booths ! My doctors office had to phone FOUR TIMES  just to get them to recognize an order  was placed. Forget I've been going there for years, each time is like I am from another planet. Once they even accused me of "washing" a prescription so I walked down the street and had the same prescription filled by CVS . NOW WOULD YOU REALLY WANT PEOPLE WITH MEMORIES THIS SHORT TO FILL DANGEROUS DRUG PRESCRIPTIONS ? I'm transferring my prescriptions to CVS !

reviews.text: Worst Wal-Mart I've ever been too. Tire and Lube express has the laziest staff and worst customer service ever. The people collecting products left out of place all over the store had aisles blocked with shopping carts while they tried to straighten out the store at the end of a day. This place is huge, convenient, but I doubt I will ever shop at this location again.  It's too bad I have to give them 1 star, they don't deserve that.

F*ck the workers in this Walmart. They are not willing to help with anything. There's a sign outside on the door that says they will be updating their lab equipment from Sept 20-22nd. My posters (which are being made for a work assignment) were suppose to be ready on the 22nd, didn't attempt to pick them up until the 23rd - still under construction. A worker asked me to come back the next day. I called ahead to make sure & customer service said I could pick up my order. I don't live or work nearby. I drove there again & had the same thing happen. Not to mention that when I went there, three employees were standing over at the stations but just ignored me! I walked away to find someone to help me. They brush it off like nothing "oh well, come back tomorrow" F*CK YOU A*SHOLES. I have never had such a bad experience with a store. This Walmart is in a good location so they probably will never go out of business but that doesn't give any of the workers a reason to be a bunch of dumb f*cks. I have dealt with ghetto stores, stores that don't have enough cashiers, etc. but I would rather be hit by a f*cking bus than to ever have to step foot in this Walmart again.
Understand they have it far more busiest business than any other Wal-Mart.  There near the Dallas Cowboys, so what would you expect?! I suggest more cashier's and friendly smiling faces.
This Walmart is ALWAYS packed no matter what time you go. Also no matter what time you go they only have 2-4 cashiers open at a time.

This is a typical low-income neighborhood Wal-mart, IE: it sucks and you should avoid it. It's not so much the people shopping there (although there are some rude folks here and there). It's that low-income neighborhood walmarts are a nightmare compared to high-end neighborhood walmart super centers. Low income neighborhood walmart means understaffed ... everyone. Need help on an aisle? Good luck finding someone. Need to check-out? Be prepared to wait 10+ minutes. There are a lot of folks shopping there using EBT / food stamps, so it boggles my mine why the cashier has to wait to call in a manager to approve he transaction all the time. This causes the whole check-out process to grind to a halt as everyone behind the EBT'er is wondering what the hold up is. Go in on a rush (eg: 7pm on a saturday), and you will wait in line a good 20 minutes to get checked out as the manager is going from cashier to cashier to approve EBT orders or something. EBT has been around for a long time, so I don't know why walmart can't expedite that. I guess there's causes of fraudulent EBT they're worried about? Either way, it's annoying as crap when you're stuck in line. The cashiers try to be as patient and pleasurable as they can when folks are being nasty to them for the wait. The walmart in Plano on 75 / Legacy and the one on Marsh & Frankford as also low-income neighborhoods and you will have the exact same experience. I filed a complaint explaining that if they know they get slammed at certain hours why don't they man more cashiers. The manager called me back, and explained that it was store policy to reduce down to 2-3 cashiers after 9pm. 9pm is when low- income walmarts usually pick up in business (due to folks working night shifts), so it boggles my mind how inept the management is at walmart that they can't notice the pattern and accomodate the check-out process with more cashiers. It's more likely that they just don't care. They don't value low-income peoples' time. You get to wait 30 min in line if you want to check-out after 9pm at places like this, because they want to save a buck and know you're willing to waste your valuable time. I've never had to wait more than 5 minutes to check-out at a high-end neighborhood walmart, even after 9pm. Everyone gets the same 24 hours in a day, that's the only thing equal about all of us. But, walmart thinks a poor person's time is acceptable to waste as opposed to a more wealthier person's time. Sad. Gf and I aren't shopping here again.

reviews.text: I switched to this pharmacy after enduring 2 years of really poor service at the CVS up the road. Every time I have been to this store they were very polite and when I call in a refill on the automated system, or when the doctor calls something in it's ready when I go. The other place you could call two days in advance and it still wasn't ready when I got there.

This pharmacy is always busy, and consistently seems to be understaffed.  Despite the work load and challenging customers, the employees exhibit composure and kindness.  During my last visit, I was told my prescription would be available in two hours (an unusually long wait time for a basic refill).  I returned two hours later, and ended up waiting another 20 minutes.  

During that time, I watched the young lady at the register.  Four customers yelled, cursed, berated, and delivered a demoralizing commentary on the inadequacies of the pharmacy.  All the while, a man was red-faced, honking his horn and yelling in drive thru.  I have never been so disappointed in my fellow human beings.  The young lady apologized, time and time again, and did her best to explain the delay...... She never lost her composure, continued smiling, and helped every customer in a courteous manner.

I am grateful for a pharmacy that can communicate a delay when they're backed up.  I appreciate the kindness of the employees.  However, I am afraid Walgreens will lose quality employees, and customers, if more of an effort isn't made to hire a staff that can adequately serve the business needs of this pharmacy.

reviews.text: This place is horrible. Always problems with the pharmacy department.  They tell me 20 minutes, and I get my prescription days later...never wait for your drugs.  If you get cosmetics, you cannot check out at any other counter except cosmetics, if you get nuts or a drink you need to check out at another counter.

Mike, the manager of the pharmacy, was extremely rude, condescending, unhelpful, insulting, and every other possible negative adjective applicable to service in this field.  I am a Doctor and was treated as if I was not a Doctor, was insulted and was forced to provide 4 forms of identification proving that I am a Doctor.  Mike continued to be rude and did not want to listen to my concerns regarding the way I was being treated.  He then essentially told me that I was not being honest and that I was trying to manipulate the system.  Apparently, this Mike the manager has been called in front of the Louisiana Board of Pharmacy for dispensing illegal prescriptions on multiple occasions.  He is incompetent and has limited knowledge of the medications that he dispenses.  For example, I asked him regarding this oral therapy for pulmonary hypertension with sildenafil.  He did not recognize the drug nor did he have any idea that this drug is commonly used to treat pulmonary hypertension.  This individual is completely incompetent and should have his license reviewed and possibly revoked.   His job should be limited to counting pills; although I am not confident that he can do this with any degree of accuracy.   I will NEVER go to this pharmacy or Walgreens for any reason due to the lack of professional courtesy provided by this so-called pharmacist.

I'm offended by waiting an hour and a half for something any monkey can do in 8 seconds. I will not go back to this place - even if it means I have to go to (gasp!) Wal-Mart.

reviews.text: My wife bought a King Cake here and it was phenomenal. This place has it all. It may look a bit shabby but the people that work there are sharp and friendly. Whoever they have ordering their liquor is on top of their game, I picked up a rare bottle of Ron del Barrilito Three Star from Puerto Rico there recently, at a decent price, too!

Don't let the shaggy appearance fool you, Dorignac's is by far the best gourmet grocery store in the New Orleans area.  I go here for the wine, spirits, bakery, and gourmet cheese mostly.  The seafood department smells like urine but I don't go that far back into the store!
A

Dorignac's has long been the preferred grocery store for my husband and I. On some products the prices might be a little higher than chain groceries, but the variety of products (especially the wine section) and the service absolutely cannot be beat. The staff are always friendly and helpful and we are always able to find what we need and get checked out in no time. Where else can you go these days where you get your own personal grocery bagger? Dorignac's has been doing things right for a long time and we will certainly keep going there for as long as they are.

I live in Mississippi, but am in NOLA often. Dorgnac's is one of my first stops in town for supplies. Bakery is excellent, and it has the best selection of local food products in town. It's also a good place for visitors to where the famous New Orleans food comes from.

reviews.text:
Just wanted the read drum brake pads replaced for the special $99. They tried to up sell me for another $300 on other items. Told them "Do the rear brakes". Then they broke the master cylinder, what?

They did replace the MC for free and finish the job. Now I have rear brakes that squeal constantly due to the horrible pads they installed. These pads cost them about $5.

Go to a real mechanic not these corporate goons who only care about the bottom dollar.

I'll replace the crappy pads they installed as soon as it gets warmer. I only went to them for convenience and hated the experience.

Always had a positive experience here, not sure why this place has a 1.8 rating...     I guess all the customers with good experiences dont bother leaving reviews.   I do however always recommend getting atleast two price quotes for major car work.

If you are one of the 1%ers by all means flush your money down the toilet here!  they will hold you down over the barrel and rip you off completely.  this is one of the BIGGEST rip offs in town!  A 300 brake job ended up costing me 1800 and the car still needs brakes.  they will hold your car hostage if you dont do what they want.  very unscrupulous business.  DONT GO THERE!

Tires plus in Morrisville Pa or any other tires plus or Firestone is the worst company to work for, or to get work done.
This is y tires plus is designed to rip off the customers, on a daily basis the management including the district manager jay Sporn demand services to be preformed on cars. These services are including but not limited to brake flushes coolant flushes alignments and other services, they demand each store to get a number of them per day so in return they push it on the customers even if they don't need it. Another scam is the complete vehicle check. 
You come in for a problem and an inspection and they charge u for both when in reality the inspection for the state is the only one you need because the mechanic has to look over the complete vehicle anyway.
Another scam is the selling if tires. They tell people with all wheel drive vehicles that they need all for tires if a tire comes in to be fixed because they can't just replace one. That is just not true you can replace 2 or even 1 if its the same tire. They will also sell people tires that are even needed. They will tell u the tire is 2 old or the tread is low and in fact it doesn't fail state inspection or violates any laws. Tires according to the state is 7-10 years old when tires plus is 4 years.
Also brakes. Tires plus will fail you for warped rotors or pitted heated rotors  or pads under 2 32nds and most of the time it doesn't fail.
The lead tech is the one that is the biggest rip off and they don't even stop him. They feed him jobs and the lead tech will tell you it will cost you over 1000 dollars to repair your car when in most cases it would be a couple 100 dollars. But he adds in extra parts that don't need to be replaces.
As you see the company should be investigated for fraud because they care scamming the customers and the mechanics will do anything to make commission.. 

DON'T NOT TAKE YOUR CAR THERE IT WILL BE A MISTAKE. IF YOU DO GET A SECOND OPINION BEFORE U GET ANY WORK DONE THERE.
Out to take your money. Poor service, with a lot of reasons to sell you new stuff. I would have give -ive, if possible.

reviews.text: It's a glorified Walmart with pathetic customer service. Employees (incld. supervisors) in this target are ignorant, uncivilized, but arrogant. Better to order online at Amazon than go to this store for anything.

As far as items, there isn't anything to complain about.  This Target has everything I need.  Produce is fresh and plentiful, meat is great, and everything else is great. In the past 5 years Ive probably had 2 instances where i experienced a fast and/or friendly checkout, and that was only because I was the only person in the store.  I dont understand why they keep hiring crap people and sticking them on the registers.  Ive never had any problems at Kroger, Wal-Mart, or Publix. reviews.text: After spending a good deal of time researching the right car for our family, we found ourselves at Henley Honda. While the car (2015 CR-V) was exactly what we were looking for, it was the customer service experience that made our final decision easier. Everyone from reception to management was welcoming, knowledgeable and friendly. Our sales associate, Omar, was extremely knowledgeable and courteous. We had been to many different dealerships in search of a car for my wife and Omar was the only one that made my wife feel included in the process. We highly recommend Omar and Henley for their vehicles, their service, and their family-oriented atmosphere. My kids told me to add the fact that Omar makes the BEST hot chocolate! They're just not allowed to drink it in our new car. :-)   The Austin's.

We picked up our new Honda this afternoon, available and ready for us just one week after we ordered it. It's beautiful to look at and awesome to drive. We are very satisfied with the friendly sales people and their fine advice. Omar is a pleasure to talk with. He is very patient with all our questions and indecisions, for we couldn't decide for a long time which car to buy. We were also contemplating a Mazda, since we have enjoyed that make as well. But we had a Honda Civic Si a few years back, and it lasted about 13 years, so we decided to go with Honda again. The deciding factors in our choice were the safety features available in the Accord Ex-L. Nadine in finance arranged sale and payment details efficiently and easily. Our insurance agent just happened to call as we were signing the papers, so we were able to arrange insurance right then and there. We were safe as we drove off the lot. Omar clearly and patiently explained many features of the automobile, and invited us back anytime for another information session. Go to Honda. Ask for Omar. Thanks to you all.

We are definite Honda fans and after purchasing our Honda CR-V from here, we are Henley Honda fans now as well. We spent a lot of time researching what car was best for us and after finding the CR-V all we had to do was find the right one for us. After visiting a couple other dealerships we came across Henley Honda. From our first phone call, to walking in the front door, to driving out of the parking lot with our new vehicle we were very happy with the service we were provided at Henley Honda. 

Our sales rep Shae was wonderful - he was incredibly easy to talk to and it quickly became evident that he loved his job and knew what he was talking about when it came to Honda vehicles. He was very courteous; he informed us of all our options but did not pressure us to purchase anything we didn't want which we appreciated. Throughout the purchasing process we had several questions and Shae always answered his phone to provide us with the answers we needed.

We highly recommend Shae and Henley for their vehicles and service.

I'm a friend Jaceks and when he was hired at honda he knew I was in the market for a new vehicle so he invited me to see the 2015 Accord EX-L.
I had been looking into getting a camry for the longest time but never pulled the trigger. Great car don't get me wrong but something didn't feel right the red stitching on all new luxury models was a HUGE turn off. 
My first drive in the EX-L was amazing and Jaceks knowledge of the vehicle  impreased me almost as much as the vehicle it's self did. I like the dual screen much better than the camry's single screen and the car just had a better younger feel. 
Went home to think about my finances knowing the accord was the right car. 
Second drive took out the touring model and the navigation blew me away. Something about the abiltiy to scroll into your exact location and out to North America in seconds makes you feel connected to the world. Buddy of mine joked that it's like a spaceship.
Since purchasing the car I have no regrets, the bluetooth is amazing. If someone calls me it's one touch on the lower screen, music stops and it feels like the person's in the car. My family and friends now know they can call me anytime my personal relationships have improved. 
Honda's reliability is obviously second to none but with the lane departure and forward collision warning you'd pretty much have to be a moron to crash this car and if you do honda link will give you a call to see if you're ok. That combined with the fuel efficiency and fact that the car is almost the identical body of the Acura made the 2015 Honda Accord Touring a no brainer decision for me. 
Can't thank Jacek and Honda enough. Jacek for helping me out with his knowledge and passion towards the industry and Honda for manufacturing the magnificant peice of machinery.

Purchasing a new car can be either be a very good experience or a very bad experience. Let me tell you my story.

This year I will be turning 30 and I figured it would be the perfect opportunity to get something nice for myself. After a few long nights researching the perfect place to purchase my new vehicle, I came across Henley Honda. With 159 reviews and average rating of 5 starts I have decided to go in and see what all the fuss was about.

Omar approached me swiftly as I entered the building and welcomed me with a big smile and a firm handshake. I was intimidated because I have never purchased a new vehicle before, this was a big step for me. Omar was very helpful in clearing up all of my questions. He made me feel right at home. Omar even took me around the whole building and introduced me to all the managers in all the different departments. This was customer service at a whole new level. I then realized, this is why Henley Honda has such a good rating.

I took a star off because when it got down to the financial agreement, it was a swift turn around. The associate was very aggressive selling the extended warranty coverage. The associate had made me feel very uncomfortable. I felt like I was obligated to purchase the warranty. I purchased the guard not because I wanted to but I felt like I needed to.

Overall my experience was amazing. If your looking for a Honda and looking for the best possible customer service that you can get, talk to Omar and tell him I sent you ;)

reviews.text: I've been a long time customer for many reasons, first and foremost is their customer service. They are absolutely honest. I have never felt taken advantage of, and they explain every repair they suggest in a way I can understand.

Best automotive service in Ann Arbor. I service all four of our vehicles with Arbor Motion and have been beyond satisfied (2 Volvos, 2 Fords.) From the loaner car availability, shuttle service and excellent communication and customer service, ArborMotion goes beyond standard . ArborMotion diagnosed a serious quality issue with my 2006 Volvo that three trips to the dealer could not. I trust the technician's expertise and experience at ArborMotion. I highly recommend ArborMotion.

This is the best automotive service one could ever hope for. ArborMotion provides the ultimate in customer service and auto care.  I've been a loyal customer for the past eight years, and have continued to take my Volvo there even after moving to Rochester, NY, and Chicago.  

At about 4:30pm on Christmas eve, I unrolled my windows and and couldn't roll them back up.  I had to drive back to Chicago on Christmas morning, and anyone who has lived through a mid-western winter knows how unpleasant driving with the windows down in winter would be. My husband suspected a fuse had been blown, so tried replacing it, twice, to no avail.  I quickly called ArborMotion and asked if they were still open.  Tim, the Operations Manager, answered and told me to bring my car in right then.  When we arrived, we noticed that it was completely empty except for Tim who had stayed behind to help me with my minor car trouble.  Tim immediately got to problem solving, and was ultimately able to solve the problem so I'd have a safe and warm drive back.  He also replaced the bulbs in one of my tail lights.  He was so understanding, kind, and helpful.  I can't imagine being crazy about having to stay behind on Christmas eve to help some lady with some dysfunctional windows, but Tim did so with the utmost of graciousness and kindness.  And, he had sent everyone home early so they could be with their families!  How amazing is that?!  I drove away feeling grateful, safe, and eager to take my car back to ArborMotion just to have another awesome experience. 

This was only the latest in amazing experiences I've had at ArborMotion.  Their customer service, professionalism, technical erudition, honesty, and quality of service keep me going back regardless of how far I have to drive to get there.  I know my car would not be in the excellent shape it is had I not been going to them for all my auto needs.  

Kind, skilled and honest people.  Incredible work.  The cleanest garage you'll ever see.  Free shuttle service.  It's the best.

Friendly staff and wonderful service! I got a full detail as well as an oil change and new tires, and the whole process was very efficient and professional. My car was in the shop for a few days, but the free shuttle service was very convenient and I didn't even miss my car while it was gone. It returned good as new! I will definitely be back. Thanks!

Fourth place we have tried, and paid good money for all tries, for car detailing.  We have found it!!!  ArborMotion did such an amazing job on my CRV, it literally is cleaner and better looking than the day I drove it home from the show room; and yes we bought it new.  

We are part of a dog rescue, and have three big lovely hair losers ourselves.  Dirty paws grinding dirt into the gray leather seats, nose art on all the windows, dust throughout the dash, and traveling crumbs from both fur and skin family it was beyond hope.  Not with Oscar and crew on the job.  Our other vehicle is going there too.  Only place we will go to from now on.

reviews.text: It's a clean and nice place for speciality foods. I like their seafood section with wild caught fish. The only thing that I don't like about this place is how their price labels are always misplaced. The price is always a couple of dollars more at the checkout from what you see on the shelf and some of the items have prices on the item and not on the shelf and if you don't look carefully, you may end up paying $7 for half loaf of bread and $9 for 6 slices of smoked turkey like I did!

Every time I visit Franklin and its surrounding areas, I stop in here. The quality of everything from the fresh produce to variety of dairy choices to its bakery is set at a much higher bar than other grocery stores nearby--the prices reflect this, as they should.

If organic, local foods is a top priority, this is your go-to place. Artisan cheeses, delicious hot bars, great assortments of vine, etc. 

The best part about this place however, is its bake shop. Not being a huge fan of sweets, I usually browse and look but rarely crave any type of cake when I'm usually out a random groceries. With a great smile and warm attitude, the friendly pastry maker took time out to ask what I usually liked and explained her favorites as well. I took home a full-sized cake that night and another few times throughout my last visit to Michigan.

Everyone will think it is a fancy market. However, the fruits and veggies are NOT fresh. We bought a box of raspberry for $5 but we literally had to throw them away within 48 hours. The celery is so old and it is too hard to chew. Everything else, even their broccoli looks very old and not fresh. We will never go back again.
This place is great, fantasitc selection and super clean. I buy my "Stakich" Brand Honey here. Delicious and locally produced!

reviews.text:
Plum Market is high-end.  For that market, it's great.  For any other standard of grocery store, it's bad (pricey).  This leaves me feeling in the middle about it.

Here are some things I enjoy about Plum Market:
- Beautiful selection of produce.
- Student discount (3%?... not as good as Hiller's 5%, I'll say that).
- Nice selection of single bottles of fancy beer.
- A well-stocked hot- and salad-bar area that also has fresh pizzas and desserts.
- Sometimes some free samples along the way!

Here are some things I don't enjoy about Plum Market:
- The prices.
- The smaller number of options per item (e.g., yogurt) than places like Hiller's
- The pizza dough you buy to bring home to make your own pizza (it's just okay)
- The attitude of the employees.
- The too-tempting arrangement of chocolate by cash registers.

For me, though, it comes down to the price and attitude.  It feels like it's trying to outdo Whole Foods.  That's not the feeling I want in a grocery store.  But maybe that's just me.
Fun place to shop. Lots of really, really good food. Expensive, but good for special treats and occasions.
Not enough stuff to choose, and prices are higher than competitors. I actually went there for the 50-15 Amex offer, but ended up find nothing worth to buy... Staffs are friendly though.

I had attended the grand opening of Plum Market few weeks ago.  This new grocery store offers everything organic.  Beautiful, clean, modern shopping experience.  Four star due to some items cost bit more compared to other places like Mariano's.  

This place also has a cafe offering Intellegentsia coffee and pastries including a chocolate bar section and frozen yogurt bar.  There is an extensive wine selections including different cheeses.  Some of my favorite local fresh products were sold here! 

Great place to shop if you live in the neighborhood and for small get-together party.

reviews.text: I believe that if you want really good eye care, Ironton Vision Center is the place to go. I would not go anywhere else.  Their staff is a great group of caring people.  Highly recommended.

I went to Dr. Patrick Milleson to have my contact Rx. refilled, due to some changes I saw in my vision.  I was immediately impressed with his assistant, who seemed very thorough, and, really knew her job well.  Dr. Milleson finished his assessment, and asked a few health questions.  He mentioned he was concerned with the pictures that he took of my eyes, and wanted me to contact my family physician, immediately.  I did the next day, and my family doctor noted the same issues.  A CT scan and lumbar puncture later I was diagnosed with IIH.  A disease that can cause blindness if not identified early.  Thanks to Dr. Milleson, I was able to be started on lifelong medications that will keep my eyesight.  I have given my opinion of Ironton Vision Center to many friends, and am happy to recommend them to anyone!  Thank you!

What I really like about Ironton Vision Center Inc. is that they are a small practice. So I feel very close to the doctors and staff their. They are all very friendly and that makes me so comfortable.
I am always very comfortable at Ironton Vision Center.  They honestly always do a great job.  I have been going there for over a decade.
I have been going to Ironton Vision Center for many years.  Their offices hours are very convenient for me.  I would recommend them to my friends and family.

I have an injury/surgery and cannot walk at the moment. Sent my 73-year-old mother in to get a few things during the snow, high priority window washing fluid. I was on the phone with her when she asked the employee for window washing fluid (she believes he was the manager). When she got to the lot she filled up the fluid which surprisingly used the whole bottle.

I got home and looked at the receipt to see why the $$ was so high...turns out the manager sold my mother Anti-Freeze, not window washer! $14 for a bottle!!! Not only is it the wrong thing, now the washer reserve is filled with fluid that just coats the window and makes it very difficult to see!!!

I called to speak with him...left a message and never heard back. Insane!!!! Shady practices!!

Place is filled with scrubs. The manager acted truculent when I asked him a simple question. I later saw him flirting with his employees and acting like he was at a party.  They need a security guard in there for the volume of scary people who are in there.  Once I witnessed a customer get in an altercation with the cabbie who brought her there when he came in and tried to collect his fee from her.  I can't understand how a multinational company has no idea what is going on in its stores.

I recently bought syringes and I need 2 different gauges to give myself the injections.  The one type that I normally use to put the serum in the syringe they were out and I told the clerk the ones that I need that the needs to be able to screw off.  She sold me some that she said would work.  WRONG!!!! The needles did not screw off and of course Walgreens wouldn't take them back and made me pay for the two that I got.  I'll be looking for a new pharmacy. This isn't the first time that I've had problems with this Walgreens.

After making 2 separate trips to this location to try to have an Inhaler script filled for my girlfriend (Out of Stock both times -  I never left the script there), we gave up and tried to get the script filled from a Schnuck's Pharmacy - only to find that it had already been marked as filled and given to customer by Walgreens staff. When my girlfriend called to fix the situation, they told her that she would need to be smarter if she wanted to abuse inhalants... Do yourself a favor and do not get your prescriptions filled here, staff is incompetent and insulting!

reviews.text:
My family and I  have been a Pharmacy and store customer for about 13 years, at 12601 Pflumm Rd Nec Of Pflumm 127th,  its close to our house. I usually have my medication called in and I drop proscriptions there all the time, I had some prescription for my diabetic pills refill left on account when I  obtained a new one from doctor and dropped it to the pharmacy in spring, to hold for future need, when I finished my medicine, I called in for a refill and the pharmacist said OK we refill, (if he didn't have it should have said I can't find your prescription we call it in again) the day after I went there in the morning to pick up and Mitch the manager was there (he is an awesome guy by the way, a good friend) and I asked to pick up, and there was a question about finding the prescription, Mitch he can see some used and unused and asked me to come back after work, he called me an hour later that it be ready tonight and wanted to confirm. 
I went there after work and the woman behind the country told me its not ready they had to call in for a new proscription, I asked why did you have to do this? We had a new prescription on file and Mitch called me that it be ready today, she was looking around, to the ceiling, up in the air, while I was talking to her, she responded, "you don't understand, we didn't have your prescription", I again mentioned about what Mitch told me on the phone, she again was looking  away up to ceiling!!!! Rude as it comes like I don't want to be here now, why are you looking up to the ceiling? I am talking to you, she said we don't have it so we called the doctor for it. another women came forward saying. you are very mean to us today........ I am standing there at awe !!!! You mean I am mean? she is looking away when I ask her a question and gives me irresponsible answers, you all had my prescription and lost it, just say we lost it, all fine, but don't look away when I am talking to you trying to explain your manager said it be ready. She started to cry. I was floored seeing this woman crying for me asking a simple question,  I said well I won't be coming back here if this is the service I am getting. .... times passed and few months later my doctor's office called some other medication in for me, these folks never responded ....I was in pain and sick ...... when I called to see if they are ready they said what store do you want it transferred to......They not only didn't fill the prescription they didn't even let me know they had it......... Customer service at its worst ............ I am myself in customer service business, when a customer talks to you and asks questions either be polite and answer or refer them to someone who can, but don't look up and around and over your shoulder and brush them off . that is rude. when confronted, don't cry, its not personal, no customer has personal problem with an employee, customer service includes problem solving . You lost my prescription, say it, you called in and got another one, fine, you called me to come pick up after work have it ready, what is it with this attitude ? My name is Homi Moshiri

reviews.text: My fiance purchased a 3ct. diamind ring from Andrews Jewelers. He walked in and asked for the best ring they had and this is what he got. The district manager did not even care and said he would personally call and had one of his assistants deal with it. The last time they attempted to fix the ring they took all of the diamonds out and "rebuilt" it... I got the ring back and it lasted 3 days and the diamonds moved. We returned the ring completely and have learned to never go to a jewelry store in the mall for an engagement ring! Do not waste your time going here!

reviews.text: If you looking for low quality good looking junk at seriously reasonable price, this is the store!  Perfect for kids room or temporary arrangements.   Most of furniture here is vereened coverd MDF, there few solid wood or steel things though.    Just don't expect things to last if you have traffic.

I bought a $300 rug from this store couple of months ago , Wife didn't like the color and tried to return it. Since I couldn't find the receipt, called their customer service and they said if I take the rug to the store, they will give me store credit. I spent about half an hour to clean and repack the rug (it was in brand new condition), about 1 hour to drive to the store and 15 min wait in line, and guess what, they refused to accept it because it was an expensive item! What pissed me of was not their return policy (which is of course awful) but the fact that I double checked with their customer service and got the confirmation from them, but the store simply said their customer service has made a mistake, and they can not accept expensive items whiteout receipt ! The manager I talked to simply said sorry and that was it!
So be careful, and don't get fooled by their smile, they promise you something and don't deliver it!  DO NOT Purchase expensive stuff from them!!!!
Found a very nice coffee table for an amazing price. Unfortunately they didn't have an end-table that I liked. Setting up the coffee table was very easy.

Trying to get what I thought was an off-the-shelf cabinet turned into a long wait to get the attention of a representative to order the simple cabinet. There is no way to track your order online and the phone support requires you to be placed on hold for more than 30 minutes. No product in stock, offsite warehouse, poor customer service, and lines add up to me not wanting to return.  What happened to the European inspired kitchen and bathroom products?  I think they should change the name to IkeaMart to better reflect the products they sell and missing custormer service.

Ikea is a great deal.  I would give it 5 stars if it would fix those crazy Family Membership machines.  I went there twice 11/3/14 and 11/5/14 and it was broken.  I found determining stock via the phone (to avoid a 48 mile round trip) a little wanting.  I called before I left the house and they told me it was in stock and when I got there, no stock.  The gentleman at the desk defused it by going off on telling me to ask them to walk the floor.  

Of course, when I did that was impossible because she was not at the store.  I called only to discover the machine problem again and so I filled out a form (which there should be a sign informing customers they can get cards at checkout).  

Anyway, service from that point out was great.
